title: indian corn stew
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add salt and pepper, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and tomato soup.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Add can of corn with its juice. Heat thoroughly.
Serve with hot French bread or corn bread.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chip beef hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cream together cream cheese and milk.
Add onion, pepper, chipped beef and sour cream.
Top with pecans and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Press firmly into ungreased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake for about 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: sugarless strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve
gelatin
in
boiling water.
Put in ice cubes and stir
with
wire whip until it begins to thicken.
Remove unmelted ice.
Stir in fruit.
Fold in whipped cream and stir gently. Place
in
refrigerator for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from refrigerator
and
pour
into
pie
crust.
May top with additional
whipped cream and garnish with fresh strawberries. Very light dessert!

title: chinese meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; shape into 1-inch balls.
Dredge in 1/3 cup cornstarch.
Pour oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; add meatballs and bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice; set pineapple aside.

title: hearty burger pizza(number of servings: 2)
directions: Prepare baking mix as indicated on package for biscuits. Divide and pat into two 8-inch pie pans, greased.
Crumble ground round over each and sprinkle with salt, pepper and spices to taste.
Pour 1/2 can tomato sauce over each.
Top with strips of cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Boil the zucchini and onion in salted water.
Mix soup, carrots, sour cream and zucchini.
Put stuffing in blender and shred.
Mix with melted butter.
Put 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour zucchini mixture in and sprinkle rest of mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil the Karo syrup and sugar for 3 minutes. Add to
the popcorn. Butter hands to shape into balls.
If desired, may be colored by adding food coloring to mixture.

title: one dish chicken casserole
directions: Layer casserole dish with vegetable, add cut up or whole boneless chicken; mix condensed soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix stuffing with butter (1 square) and water (1 cup) or enough to make stuffing moist.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: olive's apple cake
directions: Blend in order the ingredients.
Mix good.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Try using carrots or sweet potatoes for a variety instead of apples.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Add together and pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 375°
for 40 minutes.
Allow to cool for 10 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add sliced onions and cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until golden.
Sprinkle on the flour and stir for a few minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Add broth, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer, partially covered, for 30 minutes.

title: wild rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Butter 9 x 13 pan.
Brown sausage and drain.
Add to rice; mix well.
Add can of mushrooms with juice.
Mix again.
Pour into casserole.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Add oil.
Drain and rinse after cooking.
Heat vinegar, sugar, pepper, dry mustard, garlic and salt until dissolved.
Add cucumbers, onion, garlic and pimentos. Pour over cooked and drained noodles.
Stir in parsley.
Cover and refrigerate 24 to 48 hours.

title: cupcakes
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in cupcake tins for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Will make 16 cupcakes (makes wonderful tea cupcakes also).

title: swedish rolls
directions: Work together yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar; set aside.
Then beat together eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Add melted and cooled shortening; add yeast mixture.
Add alternately milk and flour. Cover bowl and set in refrigerator for several hours.
Then empty out dough onto flour covered board.
Divide dough in half; roll out first half to 1/4-inch thickness.
Brush with melted butter. Cut into pie shaped wedges and roll each wedge from outer edge to center.
Repeat with second half of dough.
Place rolls on greased cookie sheet, bending into crescent shape and let rise 2 hours. Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: coffee cake(non-diet)
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs and beat until well blended.
Add the sour cream and vanilla.
Mix the flour, baking soda and salt and add.

title: nacho dip
directions: Soften cheese and layer with chili in pie pan.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheeses are melted together.
Serve warm with nacho chips.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan. Mix all ingredients, starting with egg, oil and sugar.
Mix 2 minutes.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon together, then mix this into the sugar mixture.
Add zucchini and nuts. Pour into round Bundt cake pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop ham and green onions.
Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: carrot muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add carrots, cooking oil and eggs.
Beat with an electric mixer until combined.
Pour into large muffin pan, be sure it is greased and floured.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Makes 24 large muffins.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients until mixed. Frost the tortillas with cream cheese mixture and
roll.
Wrap in wax paper or store in Tupperware in refrigerator at least 3 hours before serving. Cut into pieces and serve with salsa.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix together onion, bell pepper, soups and cheese.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 spaghetti, 1/2 chicken and 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lobster stew
directions: Saute lobster meat in butter.
Add to a pot with the milk and cream.
Stir in 3 to 4 dashes of celery salt and cook over even heat.
Do not boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle each serving with paprika.
Serves 4.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat together.
Add flour to make a very stiff dough.
Knead the dough until smooth.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll out until very thin.
Let dry 1 hour.
Cut fine.
Shake apart.
Let dry a little more.

title: steak in mandarin sauce
directions: Sauce:
Mix beef broth, mandarin juice, mandarin rind, brown sugar and soy sauce.
Set aside.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Boil water, add noodles.
When done, drain.
In a big mixing bowl, add noodles, tuna fish, soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix until well combined.
Pour into baking dish.
Put in oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: On low speed, cream together butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and mix until blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk. Add vanilla.
Mash 1/2 cup of blueberries and stir by hand.
Add the rest of the blueberries whole and stir by hand.
Grease muffin tins (including top of pan). Pile high in each cup and sprinkle tops with sugar. Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes. Cool at least 30 minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Drop by spoonful in cake pans.
Cook at once at 350° until brown.

title: microwave peanut butter - chocolate sauce
directions: In a 1-cup measuring cup stir together the syrup and peanut butter.
Microcook, uncovered, on 100% power for 30 seconds to 1 minute or until hot, stirring once.
Serve over ice cream.
Top with peanuts.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix meal in a bowl.
Add salt, Crisco and hot water until mixture is soft enough for making into pones of bread.
Fry in hot greased skillet until golden brown.

title: vegetable-pork stir-fry
directions: Brown pork strips in oil in large skillet or wok over medium-high heat.
Push meat to side of skillet.
Add mushrooms, pepper, zucchini, celery, carrots, garlic and onion.
Stir-fry approximately 3 minutes.
Combine broth, soy sauce and cornstarch; add to skillet and cook until thickened, stirring frequently. Serve over cooked rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: broiled marinated chuck steak
directions: Five hours before serving, put steak in shallow baking pan. Combine all ingredients.
Brush steak with marinade sauce and refrigerate.
Turn occasionally and reapply sauce.
Place steak on oven rack 5-inches from heat.
Bake about 2 hours at 325°.

title: apricot pecan bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine banana and milk; add to creamed mixture, alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in apricots and pecans.
Pour batter into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan. Remove and let cool completely.

title: vegetarian sandwich
directions: Combine all ingredients.
In place of chopped onion and pimento garnish, salad dressing can be used as topping.

title: mandarin orange chicken(low-cal)
directions: Pour all but 3 tablespoons of juice in a large frying pan. Add broth, onion and ginger and place over medium heat.
Bring to a boil and add the chicken.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes. Add mandarin oranges and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add cornstarch to reserved juice and mix well. Add to frying pan.
Cook on high to reduce mixture, stirring constantly. Add salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well; squeeze excess water out.
Add the herb stuffing, butter, seasonings and eggs.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into small balls. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: e-z chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil together. Stir in chips and pecans. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Add 1 cup of hot water to Jell-O.
Add Jell-O to thawed strawberries.
Mix strawberry mixture with Cool Whip, mixing with electric mixer until well mixed.
Pour into a baked and cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate until set.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Stir in real lemon juice slowly.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell and top with small amount of graham cracker crumbs.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Continue beating with rotary beater or mixer until very stiff and glossy.
Stir in salt, vanilla and coconut.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake about 20 min., or until set and delicately browned.
Let cool. Remove with spatula.
Makes 3 doz.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into the dry ones. Stir to dampen everything.
Makes 2 loaf pans (greased) or 3 foil loaves (8 x 3 3/4-inch).

title: cabbage salad
directions: Brown in 1 tablespoon oil the Ramen noodles and almonds.
Add the noodles and almonds to the cabbage, mushrooms and onions. Pour the dressing over the other ingredients.

title: venison with sour cream
directions: Place venison, garlic and shortening in a skillet.
Brown meat on all sides over medium heat.
Remove meat to a shallow (2 1/2-quart) baking dish.
Add celery, onion and carrots to drippings in skillet and saute for 2 minutes.
Stir in water, salt, pepper and bay leaves.
Pour over venison.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat balls (2)
directions: Mix meat, onion, egg, crackers & seasoning in large dish. Form into balls, put into covered baking dish and cover with tomato soup and 1/2 can water.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Be sure to put a cover on the baking dish.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges.
Add sugar; mix and set aside 3 to 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Prepare jello as directed minus 1/4 cup of water.
When jello starts to congeal, add berry mixture and nuts.
Refrigerate to congeal.

title: caramel chocolate chip bars
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk in double boiler.
Let cool. Mix dry cake mix and remaining ingredients except chips.
Pour 1/2 cake mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 6 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle 12 ounces chocolate chips over hot cake.
Pour caramel mixture over chocolate.
Pour other half of cake mixture.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add nuts.
Stir and make a well in the center.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add pumpkin and oil.
Stir carefully into the well and mix only to dampen dry ingredients. Grease and flour a tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef and noodles
directions: *Whatever you have on your shelves will work (Lipton mushroom and beef, canned cream of mushroom).
They're all delicious.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburg and put in baking dish.
Drain most of the juice off vegetables and spread over hamburg.
Use remaining ingredients to make mashed potatoes.
Spread potatoes over top of vegetables. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: baked spaghetti and cheese
directions: In a large bowl, stir together spaghetti, cheeses, salt and pepper.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Put toasted bread on top.
Some pieces may need to be cut to fit so that entire dish is covered.
Pour boiling water over top until water level is just below toasted bread.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, Crisco and vanilla.
Add eggs, milk and flour (alternately).
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 275°.
Start in cold oven.
Check for doneness and cook longer, if needed.

title: jean's beans
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion and bacon.
Add to beans.
(If you use the barbecue sauce, you may add diced green chiles or 1 teaspoon crushed red pepper flakes.)
Simmer for 30 minutes or cook on slow in a crock-pot for 4 to 6 hours.
Good for pot luck dinners and picnics.

title: rotel and cheese dip
directions: Combine together in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: upside down pancakes
directions: Arrange bacon slightly overlapping in a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Pour syrup over bacon.
Beat eggs in 1-quart bowl until foamy; beat in remaining ingredients, except applesauce, until smooth.
Pour over bacon and syrup.
Bake uncovered in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat applesauce to just warm. Cut pancakes into 8 pieces and top each with applesauce.

title: peach crunch cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in egg.
Put peaches in baking dish.
Spread cake mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: holiday rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Combine all ingredients until well mixed.
Pour over nuts.
Bake for 1 hour. Cool.
Invert onto serving plate.
Prick top of cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into unbaked 9 5/8-inch pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until pie doesn't shake in center.

title: daffodil cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and add cold water and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Fold in flour (1/2 cup) and baking powder.
Add lemon flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add 1 cup sugar, 3/4 cup flour and vanilla.
Pour over ingredients in tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy refrigerator rolls or bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and 3 cups of the flour.
Beat thoroughly, about 2 minutes. Add egg and shortening and mix well. Add remaining flour, one cup at a time, until dough cleans the side of the bowl and is easy to handle.
Knead 10 minutes on a lightly floured surface. Place greased side up in a lightly greased large bowl. Cover with plastic and let set overnight.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place liquid smoke, soy sauce, pepper, celery salt, Worcestershire sauce, salt and garlic and onion salts in covered jar; shake until well mixed.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with large piece of heavy foil.
Place brisket, fat side up, in foil-lined pan.
Pour soy sauce mixture over brisket.
Fold foil over brisket; seal.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Yields 12 servings.

title: halpuchis (ukranian cabbage rolls)
directions: Steam cabbage until barely tender. Set aside. Brown ground beef and onion. Stir in rice, celery, horseradish, and mustard. Cook until celery begins to soften. Stir in egg. Spoon mixture into cabbage leaves. Roll and fasten with toothpicks. Place in shallow baking dish, 1 layer deep. Cover with tomato juice. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8. Freezes nicely.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Measure cooked beans and mash.
Stir into other ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in raisins and grated apples.
Batter will be stiff.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: lemon cheese sheet cake
directions: Mix oil, cake mix with pudding and 2 eggs and pour into pan. Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs and pour on top of batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine pecans, margarine and flour.
Place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until brown. Set aside to cool.

title: golden cauliflower
directions: Separate cauliflower.
Put in boiling salt water; boil, then drain.
Save 1/3 cup of liquid.
Melt shortening.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir slowly into liquid from cauliflower.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Stir in Pet milk.
Add cauliflower.

title: cornstarch cake
directions: Beat eggs until creamy.
Add sugar slowly.
Combine cornstarch and baking powder in blender at low speed.
Add egg mixture to dry mixture by teaspoons.
Add flavoring.
Pour batter into greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 375° (until inserted toothpick comes out clean).

title: green pea soup
directions: Place ham bone, water, onion and washed peas in large kettle. Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally for 1 1/2 hours or until peas are soft.
Add more water if needed. Remove bone; press mixture through sieve.
Add ham pieces to drained mixture, adding marjoram and heat until bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour.
Stir until creamy.
Add flour and stir.
Roll into one-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet. Mash with a fork to flatten out slightly.

title: hearty winter soup
directions: Bring water, potatoes, carrots and celery to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer for 10 minutes, or until vegetables are done.
Add remaining ingredients; cook, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large pan and saute onions until tender. Pour onions in casserole dish. Cover with layer of crushed crackers and Parmesan. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh stewed squash
directions: In a pot put the bouillon cubes.
Wash and slice squash.
Peel potatoes and slice up in squash and chop up onion. Coo until potatoes are soft.

title: baked chicken
directions: Cut fryer into small pieces.
Soak in beer for 2 hours or overnight.
In meantime, melt butter in large shallow pan.
Cut up garlic in small pieces or use garlic seasoning in the butter.
Dip chicken in corn flake crumbs.
Place in melted butter and garlic and bake in oven at 375° until done.
I usually cook about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Brown hamburger.
Put in slow cooker; add
rest of vegetables.
Change flavor by adding more spices or salsa.
If
done on burner, simmer for 30 minutes on medium.
Be careful not to scorch; stir often.
Freezes well.

title: cool orange salad
directions: Whip jello into cottage cheese until jello dissolves.
Add drained oranges.
Store in refrigerator as you would cottage cheese.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over all and drizzle with butter. Sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Very easy dish that reheats well.
Great for pot-luck suppers!

title: variety cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine mix, oil, egg and water.
Beat until well blended.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well ground beef, milk, oats, onions, salt and pepper. With hand, shape into loaf in shallow ungreased baking pan (11 1/2 x 7 x 1 1/2-inches).
Spread catsup over top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat milk, sugar and butter.
Pour over crumbled biscuits. Beat eggs and pour over ingredients, then add vanilla.
(You can also add cinnamon and raisins.)
Pour into well-buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Serve with sauce:
lemon, applesauce, etc.

title: apple blossom pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine apples, 1/4 cup sugar and 3/4 cup water.
Cook until apples are tender.
Reserve 3/4 cup cooking liquid.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice.
While the rice is cooling off, cook sausage. (Make sure that the sausage is cooked thoroughly.)
In a skillet, combine the rice, sausage and cream of chicken soup (also, onion if you want it).
Cook on medium heat for about 10 or 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: meat ball chowder
directions: Combine meat, seasoning,
crackers, parsley, eggs and milk. Mix thoroughly and form 40 balls.
Dip in flour.
Heat oil in 8 to 10-quart kettle.
Lightly brown on all sides.
Add remaining ingredients (except corn); add it during the last
10 minutes of cooking).
Bring to a boil and cover.
Reduce heat and
cook slow,
about
minutes
or
until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6
to
quarts.
This refrigerates and freezes well.

title: caesar salad deluxe
directions: Drop garlic into half pint jar.
Add oil, Worcestershire, mustard, paprika, sugar, salt and pepper.
Let stand several hour. About 10 minutes before serving, discard garlic and pour oil mixture over croutons.
Break 2 quarts salad greens into bowl. Arrange mandarins, quartered artichoke hearts and sliced avocado on top of greens.
Bring bowl to table.
Pour crouton mixture over top and squeeze the juice of the lemon over all.
Toss gently. Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn bread salad
directions: In large casserole dish, layer corn bread, beans, tomatoes, onion, pepper, pickles and bacon.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Melt cheeses; add garlic, nuts and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Let cool until able to handle.
Shape into logs and roll in chili powder.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Add 1/2 stick butter and Velveeta cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Put in greased casserole.
Crush Ritz crackers; mix with 1/2 stick melted butter. Spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spiced apple cider(served hot)
directions: A recipe, not for consumption, but to please the eye. Remember, we eat with our eyes first!

title: nasu no karashizuke(eggplant in hot mustard)
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise, then into small triangular pieces. Soak in salt water (1/2 cup salt and 1 quart of water) overnight.
Place eggplant in colander and pour boiling water over it.
Let cool, then gently squeeze out water. Combine remaining ingredients and add eggplant.
Mix thoroughly and set aside overnight.
Store in jars and refrigerate.

title: pizza puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour stuffing mix into 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Mix cheese, mushrooms, pepperoni and flour in small bowl.
Spoon over stuffing mix.
Beat eggs in large bowl. Stir in milk and oregano.
Pour over stuffing mix.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with heated pizza sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: date bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased oblong pan. Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut while warm and roll in powdered sugar.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Roll into ball or log in a mixture of nuts and parsley.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl combine the first 5 ingredients.
Mix soda into water and add this to the bowl.
Melt chocolate squares heating with milk to a boil, then let cool and add to the large bowl.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until sides pull from pan.

title: fruit bars (diabetic)
directions: Cut up fruits and boil with 1 cup water.
Add margarine; cool. Mix all other ingredients with eggs and dry ingredients.
Add fruit mixture.
Bake in greased 9-inch square pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Rub steak with garlic.
Combine remaining ingredients. Marinate overnight, covered tightly.
Broil or grill to desired doneness.
Slice across the grain.
(Leftover marinade may be heated and passed with meat.)

title: oven omelet
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Coat bottom and sides. Beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt until blended.
Add onions, peppers and cheese.
Pour into pan.
Bake until eggs are set (approximately 35 minutes) at 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread #1
directions: Mix
broccoli,
onion,
eggs,
cottage cheese, oleo and salt. Last,
add
cornbread mix.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas; mix with other ingredients.
Chill.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over rice. Let stand. Cook broccoli a short time. Cook onion in oleo. Mix all ingredients together with mushroom soup thinned with milk. Pour in 9 x 13 casserole and put grated cheese on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Knead lightly and make into rolls.
Place in pan that has been sprayed with butter-flavored cooking spray.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Spray tops with butter-flavored cooking spray and bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 rolls.

title: gingered chicken salad
directions: Chop up chicken.
Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle sunflower seeds on top.
May serve on a lettuce leaf or put in a sandwich.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown meat, degrease and add seasoning and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream and green onions.
Layer noodles, cheeses and meat in casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: smoked turkey balls
directions: Mix all ingredients with the smoked turkey that has been ground in food processor.
Use garlic powder, onion powder and Tabasco to taste.
Make into balls and roll in Parmesan cheese, then in cracker crumbs.
Makes about 25 balls.

title: ranch dressing cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix ingredients together with mixer or fork.
Form into a ball in bowl with a spatula.
Let harden in refrigerator.
Roll in bacon bits.
Serve with crackers.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Make jello.
Chill until shaky.
Beat with mixer.
Add cheese, drained pineapple, oranges and Cool Whip.
Beat well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or Tupperware rectangle.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef (drain); add taco seasoning and mix well.

title: dilly garlic bread
directions: Cut bread in half horizontally.
Combine butter, garlic and dill; spread mixture evenly on cut halves of bread.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until golden. Slice bread crosswise into 1 inch slices and serve immediately.

title: pecan chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch.
Mix 1/4 cup honey and 1/4 cup mustard.
Spread on both sides of chicken.
Dip in chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veg mousse
directions: Pat dry the first 5 ingredients.
Before using, add water, mayonnaise and gelatine and mix well.
Pour in mold or a bowl and let sit in refrigerator until firm.
Serve with Town House or any crackers.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together well.
Spoon over sliced cucumbers or tender young leaf lettuce.
Also delicious on baked potatoes.

title: slushy punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the boiling water, mix sugar and warm water.
Bring to a boil, let cool.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Add lemon and pineapple juice.
Freeze in plastic containers or milk cartons.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer 3 hours before serving time.
Thaw until mushy; add ginger ale.
Serve.

title: apple sandwiches
directions: Start with a shiny apple.
Cut crosswise in 1/8-inch slices. Spread peanut butter on half the slices.
Put a few raisins in the peanut butter.
Finish the sandwich by placing a plain apple slice on top of the peanut butter and raisins.

title: finger paint
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water; set aside.
Combine starch with 3/4 cup water in medium saucepan.
Add hot water and cook until clear, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and blend in gelatin. Stir to dissolve.
Add soap or detergent.
Stir in liquid poster paint for color.

title: felicia's sauce for spareribs
directions: Cover spareribs with water and 1 cup of white vinegar.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and cook for 20 minutes.
Place spareribs in baking pan.
Mix all the other ingredients in saucepan and cook together until smooth.

title: zippy carrots
directions: Place oleo and brown sugar in a saucepan over medium heat; stir until combined.
Add salt and Tabasco; mix well.
Add hot, drained carrots and toss gently until coated evenly.

title: homemade mints
directions: Mix the cream cheese and flavoring together.
Mix in sugar (use fork at first, then hands).
Knead, adding more sugar if it is too sticky.
Roll into balls about the size of a marble.
Place on wax paper.
Flatten with back of fork.
Allow to harden before serving.
Makes 80 mints.

title: mexican soup ole
directions: Place stewed tomatoes in food processor to a puree.
Pour into a large saucepan and add broth, meat, corn, garbanzo beans, olives and oregano.
Bring just to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Serves 4.
Cooking time is 15 minutes.

title: pizza eggs
directions: In an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish, microcook margarine, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 30 to 45 seconds or until melted.
Add onion and green pepper.
Microcook, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Combine eggs, milk, mushrooms, salt, Italian seasoning (if desired) and pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Microcook, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 5 to 6 minutes or until eggs are almost set, pushing cooked portions to center of dish several times during cooking.

title: shannon's favorite broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Rinse broccoli in colander until thawed.
Drain.
Arrange in shallow casserole dish, 10 x 10-inch.
Top with chipped cheese. Melt butter and stir in crushed crackers.
Sprinkle over broccoli and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix until smooth with electric mixer or blender.
Chill. Serve with vegetable sticks.

title: creamed peas
directions: Prepare frozen peas according to package; drain.
Keep warm. In a pot, cook green onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except cream.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Add cream; cook until heated.
Serves 6.

title: ms. b's jelly roll
directions: In a large bowl, beat 3 eggs until thick and lemon colored. While continuing to beat the eggs, gradually add the sugar, beating until all has been mixed thoroughly.
Add the evaporated milk, water, vanilla and flavorings all at once while continuing to mix on lower speed of mixer.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to the egg mixture.
Mix well.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan and pour in mixture.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: homemade eagle brand
directions: Put in blender and mix until smooth.
Makes same amount as a can of sweetened condensed milk.

title: baked squash souffle
directions: Beat eggs until frothy. Add rest of ingredients. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Test with knife for doneness.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: In pot, melt chocolate and margarine over low heat. Slowly add milk. Mix together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture.

title: old fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Cook last 7 ingredients and pour over peaches.

title: quick chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with milk following directions on box (3 cups); then add Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place a layer of crackers, 1/2 of the pudding, layer of crackers, pudding and top with crackers.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs.
Add bananas and sour milk.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to banana mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fettucine
directions: Cook fettucine.
Toss fettucine gently with cream, Parmesan cheese and melted butter.
Serve with Italian chicken, tossed salad and garlic bread.

title: dublin potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed; set aside.
Pare and cook potatoes; drain and cube.
While potatoes are warm, drizzle with vinegar mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar and salt; chill. Before serving, add cabbage, corned beef, onions and pickles to potatoes.
Combine mayonnaise and milk; pour over corned beef mixture.
Toss lightly.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix butter, flour and powdered sugar until blended.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll in small balls and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Shake powdered sugar on baked cookies.

title: crepes-o-fat
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, until lumps are gone and batter is watery (if not add more milk).
Use wire whisk or electric mixer. Spray pan with Pam every crepe.
Put one ladle full of crepe mixture on hot pan and then tilt pan until mixture coats as much of pan as possible.
Remember crepes are supposed to be thin - so spread batter as much as possible over pan.
Crepes will cook quickly.
Serve rolled up with jelly of your choice.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and freeze.
Serve.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven, then top with bread crumbs and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: rice chicken
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Salt and pepper chicken; roll in butter.
Brown with skin-side down.
Bake 20 minutes in 450° oven. (If not brown enough, run under broiler for a few minutes.)
Lift chicken out; pour rice, onion, pepper and pimento in pan.
Stir and spread evenly.
Place chicken on top; pour broth to cover rice.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: First make sure your turkey is thawed and is hollowed.
Keep that little pack of giblets and the neck (we've got a use for them).
Now peel completely two or three grapefruits.
It depends on the size of your turkey (we're going to stuff the bird full of fruit).
Make sure you get rid of all that white pich, it gives a bitter taste.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over chops.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: mushroom wild rice stuffing or casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes, then remove mushrooms.
Add onions, parsley and celery.
When onions turn yellow, add 1/3 cup water and the rice, salt and pepper.
Add the other 1/3 cup water and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes and serve.

title: judy's prize winning sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half. Chill 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll into 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in desired shapes with cutters.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sassy baked beans
directions: Pour the beans into a mixing bowl.
Heat the oil in a skillet and lightly saute the onions and garlic, about 2 minutes, stirring.
Add to the beans.
Stir in the remaining ingredients. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: garlic rosemary potatoes(servings:  6)
directions: Remove white papery skin of garlic.
Separate cloves; do not peel.
Combine garlic cloves and water in a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until garlic is tender; drain and let cool 10 minutes.
Peel garlic cloves, reserving garlic pulp; discard skins.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add garlic pulp, milk and margarine.
Process until well blended.
Pour into a small bowl; stir in chives and next 3 ingredients.
Peel a 1/2-inch strip around center of each potato.
Arrange potatoes in a vegetable steamer over boiling water.
Cover and steam 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Place potatoes in a bowl.
Pour garlic mixture over potatoes, tossing gently to coat.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 5 minutes.
Place chicken in large casserole dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 350° until tender.
Remove cover, heat oven to 425° and brown.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add flour. Beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes. Stir batter down and fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Let rise 15 minutes. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: no-bakes
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: chocolate steam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 16 x 11-inch pan.
Sift together in large mixing bowl sugar and flour.
Set aside.
In saucepan, mix margarine, shortening, cocoa and water.
Bring to a rapid boil, then pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Dissolve 1 teaspoon soda in 1 cup buttermilk.
Mix well and add to other ingredients.
Pour into greased pan and bake 20 minutes.
Five minutes before cake is done, bring to boil margarine, cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat and mix in 1 box sifted powdered sugar. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Mix well and pour over cake while hot.
Place lid on cake pan and wrap a wet, heavy towel around both.
Let towel remain on pan until cold.

title: apple rolls
directions: Mix as for pie crust.
Roll out 1/2 to 1-inch thick.
Spread diced apples over.
Sprinkle cinnamon and roll like jelly roll. Cut in 1-inch slices.
Arrange in baking dish which has syrup of sugar and water (dissolve about 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water). Bake 1/2 hour.
Turn off oven and leave until apples are cooked at 350° or 375° (whichever, you know your oven).

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add pineapple and jalapenos.
Add handful of pecans.
Add seasoned salt.
Mix well.
Roll into a ball or may serve as dip with crackers.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes and cook in boiling salted water; drain and cool.
Peel potatoes and grate.
Add sour cream, cheese, onions, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly; turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole, then smooth.
Combine melted butter and crumbs; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: cool whip pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together the butter or margarine and sugar; stir flour before measuring.
Add flour and eggs alternately to batter, starting and ending with flour.
Fold in flavorings and whipped topping.
Mix only until blended.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan; two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans can also be used.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken sandwiches
directions: Next dip sandwich in rolled cereal crumbs.
Place sandwiches on a cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Top sandwiches with cream sauce.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Add last five ingredients to mashed potatoes.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: flounder provencale
directions: Saute onion and celery in corn oil.
Crush the whole tomatoes and simmer for approximately 5 minutes.
Arrange the flounder in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Arrange tomato mixture on top of the flounder.
Sprinkle thyme and Parmesan cheese on top of the flounder.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: puffles
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk. Pour liquids into dry ingredients; mix well.
Beat until smooth.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: 1. Break bread into small pieces. Add remaining ingredients. Shape into cakes.
2. Fry or broil until golden brown.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Trim off large leaves.
Cut off tough end of stalk and wash broccoli thoroughly.
Cut flowerets and stem into bite-size pieces.
Mix garlic, oil, Worcestershire, salt, mustard, lemon juice and Parmesan cheese in large bowl.
Toss with broccoli until glistens.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: brew and pretzel meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cover with glaze and bake 5 minutes more.

title: seasoned broiled pork chops(chuletas de cerdo a la madrilena)
directions: Salt and pepper the chops.
In a small bowl, mix the garlic, parsley, onion, paprika and olive oil.
Heat the broiler.
Grease the pan and arrange the chops.
Spread half of the garlic mixture over the chops and place the pan 4 to 5-inches from the flame. Broil the chops about 5 minutes.
Turn.
Spread with the remaining mixture and broil 5 minutes more or until the chops are cooked through but still juicy.
Serve with mashed potatoes and Molino, a wine from the central region of Spain.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce to boiling.
Dissolve Jell-O.
Add crushed pineapple, lemon juice and 7-Up or Sprite.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Chill in refrigerator until set.

title: the next best thing to magnum p.i.
directions: Prepare bottom crust by mixing together flour, butter and pecans until crumb-like.
Press mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly golden. Cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese or chow mein noodles (or both).
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well
and
pour
into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut round steak into bite size pieces and set aside.
Chop onions into chunks as well as the green bell peppers.
Set aside. Chop bacon into 1-inch strips and place into a large heavy pot. Cook bacon slowly, stirring frequently until bacon is browned lightly.
Remove bacon and set aside.
Leave bacon fat in pot. Add onion chunks to the pot and cook over medium heat until onion is translucent.
Remove and place with bacon.
Chop green bell pepper into small bits and add to bacon-onion mix.
Add meat to pot and brown everywhere, stirring well.

title: devil's delight
directions: Prepare cake according to the directions on the box.
Results are best when using a rectangular shaped baking pan (11 x 6 1/2-inch).
While the cake is cooling, prepare the chocolate pudding.
After the cake has cooled, put in a glass rectangular baking pan, lightly greased with butter or margarine.
Spread the sour cream on top of the cake, then pour the chocolate pudding mixture on top.

title: frozen sweet pickles
directions: Combine the sugar, vinegar and celery seed; warm just to dissolve sugar.
Do not boil.
Sprinkle the kosher salt over cukes, peppers and onions; let stand 2 hours, then drain.
Pour liquid into jars over cukes, peppers and onions.
Makes 4 or 5 pints.
Put in freezer.
Thaw to use.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Arrange in baking dish. Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle all over. Bake until bubbly at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can be frozen and baked when needed.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir flour and sugar together.
Add the eggs, milk, butter, corn, salt and pepper.
Stir ingredients thoroughly and cook in oven at 350° until done.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cook for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine potatoes, sugars, flavoring and eggs; beat 1 minute or until combined. Stir in pecans. Pour in pie shells and bake 45 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: bacon-potato soup
directions: In 3 quart casserole, combine first 7 ingredients.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 13 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring once.
Stir in milk, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Cook on High 8 minutes or until heated through. Yields 10 servings.

title: hershey pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and butter.
Add eggs and cream well. Combine soda with buttermilk and add to creamed mixture alternately with flour; mix well.
Add candy, nuts and vanilla. Pour batter into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Place unthawed potatoes in an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Heat soup, margarine, cheese and sour cream over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Add chopped green onion tops to mixture.
Spoon mixture over potatoes.
Cook in oven at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy salad
directions: Place lettuce leaf on plate.
Place slice of pineapple on plate.
Cut banana in half and fit 1/2 banana into hole of pineapple, standing up.
Put little spoon of salad dressing on top of banana and let some slide down side of banana.
Put cherry on top and serve.
This looks like a candle.

title: crab imperial
directions: Into saucepan, put together milk, butter and flour.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat, set aside. Into a bowl, put beaten eggs and crab meat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add worcestershire sauce.
Then add white sauce.
Mix well and pour into a greased casserole dish or baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle on bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except evaporated milk, in crock-pot. Cover; cook on high 3 hours or 4 hours on low.
Stir in evaporated milk during last hour.
Serve topped with grated Cheddar cheese and hot corn bread on the side.
Extra delicious if you add leftover beef roast, chopped fine, midway between cooking time.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain, peel and slice.
Crumble bacon, save 1/4 cup drippings.
Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and celery seed.
Add water and vinegar.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Stir in bacon and potatoes.
Cook until heated through (about 5 minutes), tossing lightly.
Add hard-boiled eggs.
Serve hot or cold.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil.
Add rice; cook, stirring over medium heat until golden.
Add onion and cook 1 minute.
Add tomato sauce, water, seasonings, green pepper and celery.
Cover; cook over low heat for 25 minutes
or longer until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Saute on stove spinach, onion, chicken bouillon, salt, pepper and garlic powder with pat of butter, uncovered, until dry.
Beat with whisk, eggs, milk and heavy cream.
Add Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Add shredded cheese to egg mixture.
Mix well with spoon.
Use 9-inch defrosted deep dish frozen pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until golden.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in soup mix, flour, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni. Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 to 30 minutes, until heated through.

title: old fashion custard
directions: Beat with mixer.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake slowly at 350° until set.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
About 1/2 hour before serving, add the mixture of mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Cook and stir onion in butter over low heat.
Stir in flour, parsley, salt, celery salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in milk and chicken broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute.
Stir in shrimp and liquid. Serves 8.

title: beef brisket with mushroom gravy
directions: Brown beef in its own fat in large Dutch oven.
Add onion, salt and pepper; cover and cook over low heat 1 hour.
Don't add water. Slice meat on angle and return meat and meat juice to pot.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Remove meat; stir in flour until thickened. Stir in mushrooms that have been sauteed in the butter.
Pour gravy over meat and serve.

title: bean and bacon soup
directions: Combine beans and water in large kettle.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour. Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet and add to soup.
Cook onions in bacon drippings until soft.
Add soup along with bacon drippings.
Bring soup to a boil and simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: marshmallow fantasies
directions: Mix
butter,
brown sugar and flour.
Put in 9 x 9-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: lorna doone cake
directions: Crumble cookies into a 9 x 14-inch pan, then pour melted butter on top of cookies.
Cook about 15 minutes at 350°, then cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all.
Dough is easier to roll out if placed in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to bake, roll out a portion at a time 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° until light brown in color.

title: tangy cheese dip
directions: Place cheese in mixing bowl and sprinkle dressing mix throughout. Blend well until cheese is smooth. Gradually add cooking wine until creamy. Refrigerate before serving.

title: peanut butter sandwich and hot chocolate
directions: Warm milk.
Place Nestle Quik in cup and add hot milk and stir.
Place marshmallow on top (or you may use recipe for hot chocolate that is on the Hershey can; I prefer to use the Nestle sweetened chocolate).

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Press into a 9-inch square pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs well and add lemon juice, sugar, 3 tablespoons flour and baking powder.
Pour over baked crust (above).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
When done, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool and cut into small squares.

title: rabbit gravy(an 1800's recipe)
directions: Boil a chicken or rabbit (have about 1/2 gallon broth). Debone meat and add all other ingredients to broth.
Bring to boil, stir.
Remove from heat to cool and serve over cornbread, biscuits or crackers.
Gravy is not real thick.

title: banana cake cream
directions: Mix together.
Pour over white or yellow cake.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over cereal.
Let cool.
In a large bowl mix remaining ingredients; add bran.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add uncooked rice.
Add boneless chicken, salt and pepper.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over top and then pour chicken broth over top.
Cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine all ingredients together. Bake in a 9x11 inch casserole dish at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: roast turkey with mixed dressing
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Put the ham in a large pot and add the 2 teaspoons of cloves.
Boil ham for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from the heat and pour off all the liquid.
Transfer the ham to a roasting pan large enough to hold and cover the ham.

title: fresh coconut cream pie
directions: Combine the flour and cornstarch.
Add egg, egg yolk and 1/2 cup of the milk.
Stir until smooth.
Set aside.
In a medium saucepan, beat together the remaining 1 1/4 cups milk, 1/2 cup sugar and the salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture begins to boil.
Slowly stir in the flour mixture, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking and stirring until mixture is thick, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla, stirring until the butter melts.
Set aside.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Line a 10-inch pie plate with unbaked pastry.
In bowl, mash sweet potatoes and butter together until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and beat until it's custard consistency.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese or put through food grinder with pimento.
Mix with salt and mayonnaise.

title: old fashioned hot milk cake
directions: In a small saucepan heat milk, butter and dash of salt over low heat; just until butter is melted, set aside.
Stir together flour and baking powder; set aside.
In large mixing bowl beat sugar and eggs with electric mixer on medium-high speed 3 to 4 minutes or until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in lemon and vanilla extract. Gradually add flour then beat in hot milk mixture (batter will be thin).
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch floured and greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cherry pie filling salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Makes a large salad.

title: molasses baked beans
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients.
Put in lightly-greased pan (2-quart).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Yields 8 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Measure; add soda and salt and sift again.
Cream shortening, add sugar gradually and cream.
Add eggs, vanilla, oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Mix. Add flour and stir well.
Form 4 balls.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight; slice thin. Bake on greased sheet at 400° about 10 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, cream of tartar, sugar and salt. Mix shortening into mixture.
Add enough milk so dough can be handled easily.
Roll out and cut biscuits.
Place in well-greased pan and bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.

title: rhubarb-strawberry sauce
directions: Follow directions on package (of rhubarb) very carefully, with one exception.
It calls for 3/4 cup sugar, that is much too sweet. I use a scant 2/3 cup or less.
Watch carefully so it doesn't boil over (when it is covered).
It happened to me just once and what a mess.
In other words when it indicates to cover, I do not; that is cover tightly, just partially covered.
When all that is done, drop in the frozen strawberries and break it up carefully.
Yummy good, after it has cooled.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a casserole dish, layer cooked macaroni, butter, cheese, salt, pepper and add milk.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick but ono spam
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the Spam.
Bring to a boil.
Add slices of Spam and simmer until done.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Mix well.
Top with your favorite salad dressing.
Serves 4.

title: pizza
directions: Make crust according to directions on box.
Fry up hamburger. Drain.
Spread crust on cookie sheet and put can of pizza sauce on top.
Top with hamburger, pepperoni, mushrooms and cheese or any other toppings desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: teriyaki pork chops(8 grams fat per serving; 4 servings)
directions: Combine garlic salt, ginger and pepper.
Sprinkle each side of chops with garlic salt mixture.
Heat skillet over high heat until hot.
Add chops; reduce heat to medium.
Cook chops approximately 10 minutes or until no longer pink.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Add red pepper, carrot and green onions to skillet.
Cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes, stirring often.
Combine orange juice, teriyaki sauce, cornstarch and Tabasco sauce; add to vegetables.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Serve pork chops over rice.
Ladle vegetable mixture on top.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter with cream cheese until smooth. Add sugar and beat until thoroughly blended. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla and flour. Spoon into tube pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: no bake fudge clusters
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in medium saucepan.
Stir in milk and syrup.
Stir over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally to soft ball stage (236°) or until syrup dropped into cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Stir until butter is melted.
Stir in oats and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: deep fat-fried frog legs
directions: Beat together the eggs, milk and seasonings.
Gradually stir in the flour.
Set this aside and prepare the dredge by mixing together the flour, cornmeal, salt, pepper, garlic powder, onion powder and cayenne.
Add the oil to a deep fat fryer and heat. Prepare the frog legs by dipping them in the egg-milk preparation and then coating them with the dry ingredients.
Fry the legs, one pair at a time, until golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.

title: nena's chocolate chip cookies
directions: First you get some butter.
Then you put a whole bunch of chocolate chips and a little bit of sugar in a bowl.
Mix with a stir thing.
Then you take a spoon and you take out the stuff and put it on a flat pan.
Put it in the oven.
Then you cook it just for a couple of hours.
When the oven beeps, you take them out. Then when they cool down, you can eat them.
Put the rest in a cover thing so you can have them later.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar until creamy.
Add flavoring, cup of flour, baking powder, 1/2 cup milk, cup of flour, 1/2 cup milk and cup of flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in the batter.
Bake in 4 layers at 325° until light brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brian's grandpa's monster cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and brown sugar. Add by hand the eggs and vanilla. Mix together flour, oatmeal, soda, salt and baking powder. Add the remaining ingredients. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet. Make golf ball size cookies, 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for approximately 9 minutes.

title: doughnuts
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water in large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and beaten eggs.
Use bread flour and add a little at a time, kneading well to make a soft, spongy dough.
Let rise 2 hours or until doubled.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll out, one part at a time, to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter and let stand 1 hour.
Drop into deep fat (375°) and fry until golden brown.

title: pork and bean cake
directions: Soak raisins in boiling water.
Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and pork and beans.
Beat until beans break up.
Add dry ingredients to bean mixture and beat.
Add drained raisins, nuts and vanilla. Bake in 2 large loaf pans at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: connie's rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix the butter, 1 cup flour and the powdered sugar as for pie crust.
Pat into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: microwave oatmeal cake
directions: Combine oatmeal and water; microwave 3 to 4 minutes, uncovered, until mixture boils.
Stir once; set aside.
Soften butter in mixing bowl.
Add sugars; blend well.
Beat in eggs. Add dry ingredients and oatmeal mixture.
Stir until blended, pour into 12 x 8-inch dish.
(Grease bottom of dish only.)
Bake 10 to 15 minutes; turn dish once.

title: anna's beans
directions: Cook beans and meat.
Season as you like.
When almost done, add soup and recipe of dumplings or biscuits.
Cook until done.

title: sugar peas with mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter or margarine.
Add sugar peas, salt and pepper to taste; heat just until hot, tossing gently.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix flour, baking powder, spice and cinnamon together and sift. Reserve 1 cup flour mixture.
Add remaining flour mixture and milk to first mixture.
Add coconut.
Sprinkle 1 cup flour over remaining ingredients and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done. This will make 2 small or 1 large cake.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add next 10 ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: chili beans
directions: Pressure cook fresh soup beans as usual.
Brown your ground beef and add chili powder, salt, pepper and onion.
Cook on low until onion is soft.
Drain, then add your soup beans and canned tomatoes.
Heat until hot.

title: pecan crescent cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add water, beating well.
Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch crescents.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Place chicken breast between 2 slices of wax paper or Saran Wrap.
Pound with meat hammer on counter until thin (1/4 to 1/2 inch).
Sliver Swiss cheese, roll inside flattened chicken breast, sealing ends and securing with toothpicks.
Coat with crumbs. Melt butter, fry rolled chicken breast in pan with butter over medium heat until evenly browned, remove.
To pan drippings add combined water, wine and cornstarch; cook and stir until thickened.
Pour over chicken and serve.

title: garlic soup
directions: In a soup pot, over medium-high heat, saute the garlic in the olive oil until golden.
Remove from the heat and cool slightly. Return the pot to a low heat and slowly add stock, salt, pepper and bread.
Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove 2 tablespoons of the soup broth and mix with the egg.
Add the egg mixture to the soup and stir.
Continue cooking until the soup starts to thicken, about 2 minutes.
Serve!
Makes 4 cups.

title: piquant sauce
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, combine all ingredients, except cornstarch and water.
Mix water and cornstarch together; gradually stir into saucepan.
Stir frequently until mixture is thickened.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook all ingredients at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Uncover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
You may add Velveeta cheese for last 10 to 15 minutes, if desired.

title: crown o'dill halibut
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a pie plate, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dip both sides of fish steak in flour mixture.
Place steaks in buttered baking dish.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise, dill pickle, green onion, dill weed, lemon juice and seasoned salt.
Spread sour cream mixture over fish.
Sprinkle fish with cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice and cool.
Add eggs, oil, salt and cheese; stir.
Add onion, garlic, parsley and green pepper; stir well.
Grease a casserole.
Put in rice mixture and pour undiluted soup over the top.
Mix together and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
If too dry, add 1/3 cup oil.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, sugar and red hots in boiling water.
Cool, then add applesauce.
Stir several times and refrigerate. Good with turkey or pork.

title: parmesan oven fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a bowl.
Combine eggs and milk in a separate bowl; dip chicken into milk mixture, then roll in flour mixture, then cheese, then bread crumbs.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Place butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in oven.
When butter has melted, tilt dish to distribute butter evenly over bottom.
Place chicken skin side down in dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over and bake for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry-nut relish
directions: Rinse cranberries whether fresh or frozen. Place cranberries and orange juice in 2-quart saucepan and bring to boil. Allow to boil until cranberries begin to pop, approximately 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add sugar and stir well. Cool. Add finely chopped pecans and orange peel. May be used immediately or allow to refrigerate overnight for flavors to mingle and develop more fully.

title: figgy pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; add mixture to pie shell.
Arrange figs with juice.
Add rest of flour mixture.
Dot with oleo.
Top with other pie shell.
Slit holes.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, 350° for 30 minutes.

title: country green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until beans are tender.

title: baked round steak
directions: Butter round steak as you would a slice of bread, on both sides.
Sprinkle on the onion soup mix, then the can of drained mushrooms.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain off excess fat and put in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions together.
Drain off excess fat.
Add to ground beef.
Add other ingredients to ground beef and bacon mixture.
Stir well until all are blended.
Cover and cook on low from 4 to 9 hours.

title: brenda's easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Line pan with wax paper.
Place pineapple rings on wax paper in pan.
Place brown sugar over all pineapple rings.
Mix yellow cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over brown sugar and bake as directed on box.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine. Blend in flour, salt and mustard. Add milk and heat, stirring constantly. The sauce will thicken a little.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese, stirring often. Add macaroni with sauce. Top with remaining cheese, bread crumbs and a pinch of paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli louisiana
directions: Cook broccoli and onions together as directed for the broccoli.
Add the butter, soup and mushrooms.
Put in the casserole and top with the garlic cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch apple dip
directions: Stir over low heat chips and milk until chips are melted. Remove from heat; stir in salt, vinegar and cinnamon.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients three times and make a well; add oil, eggs, carrots and nuts.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb squares
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and all powdered sugar.
Cut in margarine; mix until coarse texture.
Put into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl.
Spread over hot crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Slice
onions
into
greased
casserole. Spoon 1 can of mushroom
soup over onions.
Cover	with
corn
flake
crumbs. Drizzle melted butter over the
top and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until onions are tender.

title: zero dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: lima-broccoli casserole
directions: Combine well the cream of mushroom soup, onion soup mix and sour cream.
Add frozen lima beans (cooked) and chopped broccoli (cooked). Cover with seasoned croutons.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: sorority punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 7-Up and Sprite.
Freeze. About 45 minutes before serving, add 7-Up or Sprite.

title: chocolate caramel crunch
directions: Butterscotch or peanut butter chips may be substituted for chocolate chips.
One-half cup chopped nuts may also be used.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes until tender.
Melt butter in saucepan.
slowly blend in flour with whisk until well blended.
Gradually add milk whisking constantly.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cut potatoes in halves, scoop out, and set aside.
When milk mixture is very hot, whisk in potatoes.
Add green onions.
whisk well and add sour cream and crumbled bacon. Heat thoroughly.
Add cheese a little at a time, until all is melted in.
Garnish with chives, grated cheese and bacon crumbs.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
This mixture can be frozen until ready to use.
When ready to use, add 1 quart ginger ale to each 1 quart of mixture.

title: dijon-garlic dressing
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together all ingredients until well blended.

title: five bean bake
directions: Saute until tender the sausage, celery and onions.
Drain liquid from all the beans.
Mix everything together in a large baking pan.
Cover mixture with strips of bacon and bake at 350° for approximately 2 hours.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all except bread and place in carved out center of bread. Dip bread pieces in and enjoy!

title: cool whip cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Top with pineapple followed by pudding.
Top off with Cool Whip.
Allow cake to cool before layering with pineapple, pudding and Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, syrup, salt, margarine and vanilla; mix well. Add eggs and pour into pie shell. Sprinkle pecans over all.
If time, arrange pecans in circles on top of pie.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes until sharp knife inserted in pie should come out clean.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and cooking oil.
Let set 1 hour.
Add all other ingredients to apple mixture and stir enough to mix well. Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: marinade for barbecue or steak
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Makes 3 1/2 cups marinade.

title: homemade boursin cheese
directions: In a large bowl, mix or knead all ingredients thoroughly. Transfer to an appropriate cheese dish/mold and refrigerate.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Beat sugars, oil, eggs and vanilla together.
Add flour, oatmeal, corn flakes, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Roll into balls or drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crab treats
directions: Mix the three ingredients together until well blended.
Spread on split hot dog rolls and place under broiler.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil for 15 to 20 minutes. Put into sterile jars and seal.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine mashed bananas and sugar.
Stir in melted butter, then add egg and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven in prepared loaf pan.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix the jello with the hot water; add cold water.
Stir in pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into dish and let mixture set.
Cook pineapple juice, sugar, egg, flour and butter until thick and let cool.
Spread over jello.
Soften the cream cheese and mix with Cool Whip. Spread on top of mixture.
Chill well.

title: golda young's biscuits
directions: Mix flour and Crisco by hand.
Stir in buttermilk with spoon until you have stiff dough.
Work dough on floured board until ready to roll out.
Bake at 425° to 450° until brown.

title: wes' homemade crackers
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then add water.
Will make 1 cookie sheet and 1 pizza pan full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple salad (dessert)
directions: Mix the margarine, sugar and pretzel sticks and put in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: christine's casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Pour beans over this.
Repeat cheese and tortilla layers.
Mix soup and Ro-Tel together.
Pour over layers.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: eggnog
directions: Peel back one peel; slit down the center.
Fill cutout with chocolate chips and mini marshmallows or butter, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Place peel back.
Wrap in foil and warm.
Eat with a spoon.

title: chewy granola cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, oats, wheat germ, baking powder and salt. Mix well. Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat brown sugar, margarine and honey until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs. Blend well.
Add flour mixture and mix well. Stir in raisins, almonds, sesame seed and sunflower seeds. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Mix all cheeses together.
Set aside 1/3 of the cheeses and mix rest in the cooked macaroni.
Spray casserole dish and put macaroni and cheese mixture in casserole dish.
Put the remaining cheese on top of mixture. Put a layer of bread crumbs on top.
Add milk.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden.

title: light and lively
directions: Combine in a large bowl.
Mix well with mixer.
Pour in a serving dish.

title: fettucine with tomatoes and basil
directions: Blanch tomatoes in boiling water for 30 seconds, then transfer to cold water.
Skin can now be easily peeled off.
Dice and seed tomatoes.
Prepare pasta according to package directions. Meanwhile, saute the onion and garlic in the olive oil in a nonstick pan until onion is tender.
Add the tomatoes, minced basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring frequently.
Mix sauce with the drained pasta; transfer to a serving dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and garnish with basil leaves.
Yields 4 servings.

title: asparagus loaf
directions: Beat the egg slightly.
Add the heated milk gradually and mix. Add the cracker crumbs, melted butter and onion.
Let stand for a few minutes until the crumbs absorb some of the liquid.
Fold the asparagus into the mixture carefully and season with salt and pepper.
Pour into a buttered loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve from the dish.
Asparagus Loaf may be served with a cream sauce and garnished with crisp strips of bacon.

title: almost a symphony cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions, using milk instead of water. Bake in large oblong pan (9 x 13-inch). When cake is done, take out of oven and punch holes in it using a straw.
Have the sugar and pineapple with juice come to a boil.
Pour this on hot cake.
Let cake cool completely.
Mix cream cheese with mixer and slowly add the cold milk and vanilla pudding mix.
Spread this on cool cake and let cool in refrigerator a few minutes so pudding will set.
When set, cover cake completely with sliced bananas. Cover bananas with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped cherries, pecans and coconut. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and put in medium size baking dish.
Spread with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Pour 1/2 stick melted butter
over
top of cracker crumbs.
Bake in 375° oven until cheese
melts
and
becomes
bubbly
(25 to 30 minutes). Serve warm.

title: nifty sweet potato biscuits
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cook chicken until it is done enough to shred.
Save broth and remove chicken.

title: crab-avocado-papaya salad
directions: Peel and slice papaya or section grapefruit.
Peel and slice avocados.
Sprinkle with lemon juice to prevent darkening.
Add crabmeat and nuts and mix all together.
Add Lemon-Tarragon Dressing.
Border bowl with lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon fluff bars
directions: Put the dry angel food cake in pan.
Pour the lemon pie filling over
the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a jelly roll pan.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix grated cheese and margarine together.
Add dry ingredients to cheese mixture.
Dough will be very stiff.
Roll about 1/4-inch thick and cut into small biscuits.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 25 minutes or until done, but do not brown.
Makes about 125 small biscuits.

title: little applesauce muffins
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and mix.
Beat in applesauce.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture; stir just to moisten.
Spoon into mini muffin cups, greased.
Bake at 425° 15 minutes until golden.
While still warm, dip tops or all sides into melted butter and cinnamon sugar.
Serve warm.
Makes 36.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Prepare Bundt pan; spray with Pam.
Place crushed nuts in bottom of pan.
Place frozen rolls over.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Sprinkle dry pudding mix over.
Bring butter and brown sugar to a boil; pour over rolls.
Place on counter overnight or let rise for 6 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: stuffed pheasant
directions: Salt and pepper bird outside and inside and then dress bird with bacon strips.
Combine stuffing ingredients, stuff bird, tie the legs so the stuffing won't fall out and then grill over a medium fire until done.
Depending on the size of bird, time will vary.
A good rule is that when you can turn the leg bone easily in the socket, the bird is cooked.

title: grandma lunts buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients in bowl (just place and stir with fork).
Cut shortening in with pastry blender or two knives.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk. Add yeast and extra flour if needed.
Can let rise about 10 minutes in warm place before baking.
Bake at 400° until light brown on bottom (15 minutes).

title: caramel frosting
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in a large iron skillet.
At the same time, be cooking other mixture. (Mix egg with sugar, then add milk and oleo.)
When sugar gets brown, pour mixture into skillet and boil until thick (will be thick enough when you can pull spoon through it and see bottom of skillet).
Remove from heat and beat until cool enough to spread.

title: chocolate chip cookies
