directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet or electric frypan. Combine biscuit mix, salt, egg and beer; mix until smooth. Dip fish into batter, letting excess drip into bowl.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Place zucchini in microwave-safe dish.
Cover and cook on High 5 minutes; stir in mushrooms.
Cover and cook 5 minutes longer. Drain off liquid.
Set aside.

title: traci's blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift 2 cups flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add sifted ingredients to sugar mixture and beat.
Dredge blueberries in remaining flour.
Fold berry mixture gently into creamed mixture.
Pour into a buttered and sugared tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: claudette wallace's chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix cocoa and powdered	sugar.	Stir
in
margarine and enough milk to make icing	of
proper consistency to spread on cake.

title: unleavened bread
directions: Mix like pie dough; roll thin and place on cookie sheet.
If you want individual pieces, cut with pop cap on cookie sheet. Punch out after baking.
Makes 50 to 70 wafers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or less (check often so they don't burn).

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Place chops in sprayed baking dish with a top cover.
Cover top of chops with ketchup, a slice of tomato and a slice of red onion.
Sprinkle with dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Pour enough of sherry to cover bottom of dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Remove cover and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: vegetables and rice(low-fat)
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 50 minutes, or until moisture is absorbed and rice is tender.
Melt margarine in a heavy skillet; add onion and green pepper.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Add water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce, salt and pepper; stir into rice.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onion and peppers.
Let stand overnight.
Add pickling spice, sugar, turmeric and vinegar.
Cook until tender. Put in jars and seal.
Makes approximately 7 pints.

title: potato and bacon salad
directions: Drain potatoes; cube Velveeta cheese.
Crunch bacon.
Add mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper to taste to the rest of the ingredients.
Fold all together and pour in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: quick berry dessert
directions: In large bowl cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Butter 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Turn mixture into pan.
Spoon pie filling into the cake in 16 spots spacing it evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Filling will sink into the cake while baking.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Cream sugar with Crisco.
Dissolve with boiling water.
Add ice water and yeast; beat in eggs lightly.
Mix in flour and salt. Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
(Dough can be kept in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.)

title: pita bread(khubaz)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Let stand for 5 mins.
Stir in salt and mix in 3 c. flour to form a rough sticky dough.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, adding flour if necessary.
Divide dough into 8 equal parts and shape each into smooth ball.
Flatten each slightly and roll into 5 inch circle.
Put rounds on baking sheets, cover with cloth and let rise 45-60 mins. or until lightly puffed.
Preheat oven to 450° and bake rounds 8-10 mins. or until lightly browned.
They will puff up while baking.
While still warm, put in plastic bag, leaving one end open.
Keeps bread moist and pliable.
Makes 8 loaves.

title: pecan pie
directions: In mixing bowl, slightly beat eggs.
Stir in corn syrup, brown sugar, salt, pecans and vanilla to mixture.
Pour into a regular pie crust shell.
Bake at 375° until center is set when gently shaken, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Crush bananas and whip until light.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until toothpick tester comes out clean.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Mix margarine and cheese.
Add flour, salt and pepper; mix well, then add Rice Krispies.
Mix well and form into small balls. Place on cookie sheet and flatten thin.
Cook in preheated oven at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie(microwave)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole crumble beef.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook covered on 100% power for 4 to 6 minutes, stirring once.
Drain fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, flour, basil and fennel.
Cook uncovered on High 6 to 8 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.
Cover and set aside.

title: blue ribbon kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cut in half (unless you use small ones to pickle whole).
Combine salt, vinegar and water.
Heat to a full rolling boil.
Add garlic to boiled mixture, then remove garlic and put 4 halves in each sterilized jar.
Pack cucumbers in pint jars.
Add 2 tablespoons dill seed and 3 peppercorns to each jar. Fill with pickling liquid 1/2 inch to top of each jar.
Immediately adjust jars.
Process 15 minutes in waterbath canner.
Remove from canner and complete seal.
Makes 7 pints.

title: dove with dried beef
directions: Layer dried beef in baking dish.
Wrap each dove breast in bacon and place on dried beef.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream. Pour over breasts.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
Serves 4.

title: bavarian peach cream
directions: Prepare Jell-o according to package directions. Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites. Beat gelatin at high speed in mixer until foamy, about 2-3 minutes. Fold in whipped cream and peaches. Pour into a lightly oiled 6 cup mold. Cover and chill overnight. Unmold before serving.

title: blender pumpkin pie(no crust pie)
directions: Put all in blender for 1 minute.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: grilled lake trout
directions: Mix steak sauce, lemon juice, thyme, basil, oregano, parsley, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese with mayonnaise.
Place the fillets, skin side down, on a medium-hot grill.
Spread the mayonnaise mixture on the fillets and cook for 15 to 20 minutes. Use a piece of foil to over the fillets lightly so that the mayonnaise mixture browns.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Make into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini carrot cake
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
Add oil and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat with electric mixer for 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in carrots, zucchini and nuts.
Pour into a lightly greased 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel jello
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before adding next layer.

title: spinach enchilada
directions: Melt down frozen spinach in a covered saucepan without water. Add onion soup mix, cottage cheese and half of Monterey Jack and Swiss cheese.
Stir until melted.
Spoon ingredients into uncooked tortilla folded like a burrito (sides folded in and ends rolled). Line up in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Pour whipping cream over top (not whipped).
Cover with foil.
Bake covered at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover for 15 minutes until top browns.

title: frances' pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco. Add sugar, then add eggs, one at a time. Blend after each egg. Sift flour twice and add alternately with milk. Add baking powder and lemon extract. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick chili
directions: Cook hamburger.
Drain.
Put in a large pan.
Add Ro-Tel, kidney beans and pinto beans.
Cook until desired consistency.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Put yams and apples in buttered 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in mustard and orange and lemon juices.
Drizzle over casserole.
Bake covered for 45 minutes in 400° oven.
Baste frequently.
Sprinkle with coarsely chopped walnuts and bake uncovered another 15 minutes at 350°.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter or margarine.
Gradually add sugar, while beating.
Beat until light.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spoon into a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan or bundt pan. Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: brian's enchiladas
directions: Brown burger and mix with taco seasoning.
Saute hot peppers (whole) in butter.	When done, cut in half and remove seeds and stem.
Put in peppers in blender and puree.
(Add a little water if needed.)
Mix peppers and soup in bowl.
Lightly fry corn tortillas in deep fryer and then dip in soup mixture.
Lay a layer of coated tortillas in a 9 X 13 pan.	Add layer of 1/2 meat, add layer of 1/2 cheese, then repeat layers.
Then add final layer of tortillas, put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until warmed through, about 30 minutes.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Saute the onion and celery in the butter. Add the soup, broth and soy sauce. Add the chicken. Top with the noodles and nuts. Place on bottom rack of oven. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: garlic cheese spread
directions: Microwave Cheez Whiz until smooth.
Allow cream cheese to soften at room temperature.
Cream the Cheez Whiz and cream cheese together until creamy and smooth.
Add small amounts of garlic powder until desired taste is achieved.
Use for dipping veggies or spread on French bread.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Put sliced apples in a 9-inch pan.
Toss with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix together flour, sugar, melted margarine and egg. Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl, mix water, yeast, sugar and salt. Add 1 1/4 cups flour and mix well. Add egg and oil; mix in 1 1/4 cups flour, mixing well. Cover and let rise at room temperature until double in size. Turn out on lightly floured surface. Knead lightly; pinch off rolls. Place in oiled baking pans. Let rise until double in size. Bake in 400° oven until brown.

title: curried meatballs with chutney sauce
directions: Prepare chutney sauce.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix remaining ingredients; shape into forty-eight 1-inch meatballs.
Place in rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake uncovered until light brown and no longer pink inside, 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot with chutney sauce and wooden picks.
Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: mrs. ethel's fruit cake
directions: Use all flour on fruit; cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs; add flavorings and combine all together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: beef-carrot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion until done and drain.
Add all other ingredients (except noodles and cheese), saving the cooked noodles until last.
Mix well.

title: beef and beer casserole
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet; brown meat in oil.
Season with ground pepper and remove to Dutch oven.
Melt margarine in same skillet; add mushrooms and onions and sprinkle with flour.
Cook and stir mushrooms and onions until onions are tender.
Put mushrooms, onion, etc. into Dutch oven with meat.
Add beer and simmer, uncovered over low heat, stirring occasionally until meat is tender, about 2 hours.
Stir in pepper to taste and hot sauce. Cool.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: custard angel squares
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or pan with angel food cubes. Combine gelatin and 1/2 cup sugar in top of double boiler; stir in salt, milk and 2 egg yolks, slightly beaten.
Cook, stirring over simmering water until mixture coats metal spoon with thin, even layer.
Add vanilla.
Chill or stir over ice water until thick, but not set.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until soft peaks form.
Fold whipped egg whites and whipped cream into thick custard.
Pour custard over cake and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Cut in squares and top with butterscotch sauce.

title: spiced pecan halves
directions: Melt margarine in shallow baking pan. Stir in seasoning and Worcestershire sauce.
Add pecan halves.
Mix until nuts are coated.
Heat in a 250° oven for 60 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Cream together	cheese and Amaretto.
Mold.
Serve with fresh apples, pear wedges and strawberries.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and mash in a bowl.
Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Enjoy with cocktail ryes, crackers or veggies.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and chill for several hours.
Form into a ball and roll in mixture of chopped pecans and chopped parsley.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening and peanut butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend in syrup and milk.
Shape into a 2-inch roll.
Chill.
Slice 1/4-inch thick. Place half the slices on ungreased cookie sheet; spread each with 1/2 teaspoon peanut butter.
Cover with remaining slices.
Seal edges with fork.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from sheets.
Makes 2 dozen.
Cookie dough can be made one day and baked the next.

title: cream cucumber
directions: Pare cucumber and slice very thin.
Put into bowl; add salt and place in refrigerator.
When cold, press cucumber slices between the hands to remove the salt.
Rinse in cold water.
Add sliced onion; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over cucumbers.

title: orange dream salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press on bottom of pan, saving a little to sprinkle on top when finished.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour on top of crust.
Freeze and take out 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: sausage and egg brunch
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk and salt.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Store in refrigerator covered overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields:
6 to 8 servings.

title: wine biscuits
directions: Mix sugar, baking powder and wine.
Add oil.
Slowly mix in flour.
Roll dough in small balls.
Then roll out on counter. Fold in half, twist and join at ends.
Place on greased cookie sheet in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Pop popcorn and set aside (2 cups peanuts may be added). Combine sugar, margarine, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil. Boil, without stirring, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popped corn, stirring until corn is covered.
Bake in shallow pan for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread avocado dip; sprinkle olives and cheese. Top with picante sauce. Chill approximately 1 hour. Serve with nacho chips.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and slice thinly.
Fry bacon until crisp. Mix potatoes, onion, oil, salt and pepper.
Add crumbled bacon and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add sliced hard-boiled eggs and mix in gently.
Note:
Mixing with your hands is better than with a spoon as it is easier to feel the consistency after adding oil and mayonnaise.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In large mixing bowl, on low speed; combine cake mix, 1 egg, margarine, and 2 tsp. pumpkin pie spice.
Do this until mixture is crumbly.
Press onto bottom of jelly roll pan.
Set aside.
In another large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk, remaining eggs, remaining pumpkin pie spice, and salt.
Mix well. Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with nuts (optional).
Bake 30-35 minutes or until set.
Cool and then chill until ready to serve. Keep refrigerated.
Yields 20 bars.

title: peanut butter peaks
directions: Put margarine, peanut butter, 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and egg in large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Shape dough into balls and roll in 3 tablespoons sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes.
Place a kiss in center of cookie; press gently.
Continue to bake 2 to 4 minutes until chocolate melts slightly.

title: baked carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
With mixer, beat until they are mashed.
Add other ingredients while you beat carrots.
Place in a casserole and bake at 350° until it sets, about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: slushy punch
directions: Dissolve jello in
boiling
water.
Mix
sugar and warm water, bring to a boil and add to jello.
Let cool.
Add lemon and pineapple juice;
mix
well.
Freeze in plastic containers or Ziploc bags.
When
ready to serve, remove from freezer and let thaw until you can
divide
it
in pieces with a knife and mash to a slush with
a
potato
masher
(about
3 hours for a gallon size container).
Add ginger ale and serve immediately. (The flavor of the
jello
determines the color of the punch.) Very good.
Yield: 50 small punch cups.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Cream margarine; add grated cheese.
Mix in flour, salt, cayenne and pecan halves.
Roll in balls.
Press pecan half on each.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and let stay in oven another 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix together jello, pineapple, sugar and water and boil 10 minutes.
Slowly put in bowl to cool.
Whip cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Cream together, then mix with other ingredients.
Chill.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix cake mix and poppy seeds.
Slightly beat eggs, oil and water.
Add to the cake mix and beat 4 minutes. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 45-50 minutes at 350 degrees. I like this recipe because it makes two loaves, one for the family and one to give away.

title: old-fashioned pot roast
directions: Place roast, potatoes, carrots and onion soup in a covered roaster; season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours and 30 minutes.
Combine mushroom soup and water; pour over roast and continue baking for 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk in a large size electric frypan.
Set control dial at 280°.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off frypan.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows and peanut butter are melted and blended.
Turn into a buttered 8-inch pan and cool before cutting.

title: fried green tomatoes with rock shrimp salad
directions: Season the shrimp with salt and black pepper.

Combine the water, liquid crab boil, lemon and bay leaves in a large, heavy pot. Season the mixture with more salt and black pepper. Bring the mixture to a boil; add the shrimp and cook for 1 minute. Remove from the heat and let sit for 1 minute. Drain and discard the liquid. Let the shrimp cool to room temperature, then refrigerate for about 2 hours.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels and half of the evaporated milk.
Set aside.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
In a large bowl, mix the following:
melted margarine, dry cake mix, other half evaporated milk and nuts.
Stir by hand until well mixed.
Press half of dough in cake pan.
Bake 6 minutes, then sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Spread on caramel mixture.
Dab on remaining dough.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil; simmer until cauliflower is tender (about 15 minutes).
Put through a blender, a bit at a time.
Return to pan; add whipping cream, nutmeg and salt.
Heat to a simmer.
Serve in bowls with a dollop of butter and a dash of nutmeg.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Microwave bouillon cubes in 2 cups of water.
Bake tostado shells per instructions on box.
Break up into medium to large pieces.
Fry onions in a small amount of oil.
Add tomato sauce and picante sauce.
Add cheese soup to bouillon broth and whisk until creamy.
Mix all together in 6 cups of water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce to simmer.
Mix tostado shells in and serve with grated cheese on top.

title: pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Add salt and flour.
Knead dough on floured board until smooth (3 to 5 minutes).
Cut off 4 inch pieces of dough; roll into ropes 6 to 8 inches long.
Twist into pretzel shapes.
Arrange on lightly greased cookie sheet. Brush egg over tops (those places missed will not brown).
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Pretzels will be shiny brown.
Serve within two days or freeze for later.

title: spiced raisin sauce for ham
directions: Mix
brown
sugar
and	spices in top of double boiler. Stir in	water and vinegar.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce comes to a boil and is thick and smooth. Stir
in
raisins.	Place over boiling water and cook until raisins are plump.	Stir in oleo.
Store in refrigerator until ready
to serve.
Serve hot.
Will keep in refrigerator about 1 month.

title: pork chops
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Dip in egg and cornflakes. Place in baking dish lined with foil and bake at 250° for 1 hour. Yields 6 servings.

title: banana loaf cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 2 loaf pans at 275° to 300°.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar in mixer on medium speed.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Add your favorite pie filling and top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: Grill vegetables and baste with dressing.

title: party beets
directions: Mix syrup from 1 can pineapple chunks with water and vinegar. Stir in brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cook about 10 minutes. Add pineapple and both cans of drained sliced beets.
Serve hot.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Combine all ingredients except fruit, making a thin batter. Pour into baking dish to which 3 tablespoons of melted butter have been added.
Then pour sweetened fruit into the middle of the batter.
Bake at 350° to 400° about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ham and egg supper
directions: Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to corn liquid to make 1 1/4 cups.
Chop luncheon meat fine.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until set.
Yields 6 servings.

title: john wayne casserole
directions: You will need 3 bowls.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Put flour, salt, sugar and egg in a bowl.
Add buttermilk until batter is slightly thick.
Dissolve baking soda in boiling water (about 2 tablespoons).
Mix well into batter.
Preheat griddle on medium heat.
If griddle is preheated, you will not need to grease it.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, alternate layers of batter and blueberries until all is used. Cut butter into reserved cake mix and brown sugar.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spread over batter and blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: crab ball
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese, crabmeat and lemon juice. Mix and mold into round ball (can freeze at this point).
Place on lettuce leaves and pour cocktail sauce over entire ball when ready to serve.
Garnish with parsley and serve with crackers.

title: choco-peanut butter squares
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the flour, brown sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Add the peanut butter and butter and blend at low speed until crumbly.
Remove and set aside 1 cup.
To the remaining mixture add the milk, eggs, and vanilla.
Blend at low speed until moistened then beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle chips over batter.
Then sprinkle on the reserved crumbs. Bake for 40-45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: company coming casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a well-greased casserole dish.
Top with 1 stick melted butter and 1 stick crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday smells
directions: In a medium sauce pan, (Vision Ware works great for this). Add water, 1 orange (cut up), red hot candy (for color), a few whole cloves, 1 or 2 cinnamon sticks, (optional). Bring all ingredients to a boil, lower heat to a low settings, (just warm).

title: peppermint stick punch
directions: In punch bowl combine all ingredients, except club soda and candy canes.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add club soda. Hang candy canes on edge of punch bowl or place in each punch cup for stirrer.
Makes about 1 1/2-quarts.

title: hamburger salami
directions: Mix well and cover. Refrigerate for 3 days.
On the fourth day, make 3 rolls 2 1/2 x 8-inches.
Bake on broiler for 10 hours. Makes 10 servings.
Oven temperature: 150°.
Time to prepare: Minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, salt and flavorings.
Slowly pour in milk.
Mix well.
Add to 9-inch pie shell, add nutmeg to top of pie.
Bake on lowest rack of oven at 375° for 30 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and boil.
Mix sugar and flour and 2 eggs (well beaten).
Add buttermilk or the milk with the vinegar in which you have added the 1 teaspoon of soda.
Add vanilla.
Now add the first three ingredients.
Put on an oiled cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Can add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and nuts, if desired.
Ice while still warm.

title: almond cookies
directions: Combine and drop by 1/2 teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat to boiling crushed pineapple.
Stir in large jello.
Let cool.
Stir in buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Chill until set.

title: sally's punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions (cool).
Mix two cups boiling water with Jell-O.
Add frozen berries; stir until syrupy.
Make pudding according to package.
Let set.
Use large punch bowl. Layer with torn pieces of cake, then strawberry mixture, then pudding.
Continue each layer until all ingredients are used. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and serve.

title: dreamsicle pie
directions: Mix sour cream, Cool Whip and Tang together.
Spoon into crusts.
Top with Mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate; let chill and serve.

title: swiss sandwich loaf
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Slice bread 11 times. Fill every other slice with cheese mixture.
Wrap loaf in foil. Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat dish(club member: mindy daniels)
directions: On large platter, spread cream cheese. Drain and squeeze juice from crabmeat. Sprinkle over cheese mix. Mix horseradish with catsup and cover top of crabmeat. Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except crabmeat in double boiler.
Mix in crabmeat and heat but don't boil.
Serve warm.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Stir in sour cream, then stir in 1 large Cool Whip.
Place layer of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix.
Repeat layers.
Put remainder of Cool Whip on top for dressing.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar with hot water.
Let cool while preparing fruit.
Chop cranberries and add to chopped fruit.
Add nuts, sugar and jello.
Chill.

title: 7-layer dip
directions: Mix refried beans with taco seasoning.
Spread this mixture on bottom of large plate or serving tray.
Layer remaining ingredients in order they appear.
Use own judgment on amount of cheese.

title: danish sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll in small balls.
Put balls in greased cookie sheet and mash down with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 minutes.

title: sta-soft frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick; cool completely.
Beat Crisco, margarine
and sugar together for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add cooled mixture
to	this along with 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat 5 minutes more.

title: easy brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket liberally with meat tenderizer; then salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Line a baking dish with foil and place brisket on foil.
Pour about 1/4 cup smoke sauce over brisket and seal tightly in foil.
Bake at 300° to 350° for about 2 1/2 hours for a 3 pound brisket or 5 hours for up to 7 pound brisket.

title: oriental pork and vegetables
directions: Soak onion flakes in water for 10 minutes.
Cut meat into 1-inch cubes. Heat oil in large kettle.
Add pork and cook 5 minutes to brown on all sides.
Add onions, ginger, garlic powder and red pepper; cook 5 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add mushrooms and cook 3 minutes longer.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Add to pork with pineapple.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour or until pork is tender.
Blend cornstarch with soy sauce.
Stir into pork and simmer, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add pea pods.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: cocktail party tray
directions: In 3 separate plastic bags, combine shrimp, chicken wings and chicken strips each with 1/2 cup chili or hot seafood sauce. Marinate in refrigerator a few hours or overnight.
Remove from sauce.
Broil or grill until done, turning frequently.
Serve with cocktail sauce.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 12 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with crushed flakes.
Drizzle with one stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: joan's gold punch
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and freeze.
Add ginger ale at time of serving; mixture will be slushy.
May add fruit ring.

title: ham loaf
directions: Press into pan or baking dish.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, then drain.
Pour in large mixing bowl.
Dice up onion and eggs; add to potatoes, then pour in remaining ingredients.
Mix all together good, then serve.
Also good chilled.

title: duchess potato puff
directions: Lightly butter 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In medium saucepan, heat water, margarine and salt to rolling boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in milk and potato flakes.
Blend in egg, sour cream and cheese, mixing thoroughly.
Spoon into prepared casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until lightly golden brown and puffed.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: aunt becky's london broil
directions: Rub 1/4 teaspoon black pepper and 1 1/4 teaspoons tenderizer on each side of meat.
In frypan, heat the oil.
Let pan get hot (425°).
Add the margarine.
Cook 5 minutes on each side (cooking time for rare, which is best).
Slice thinly; place on platter. Make au jus by adding 1/4 cup water.
Scrape bottom of pan while simmering 2 to 3 minutes on high heat.
Pour over meat and serve.

title: tabbouleh salad
directions: Place bulgur wheat in medium bowl and cover with water for 10 to 15 minutes. Squeeze out excess water that is not absorbed. Mix lemon juice, cumin, garlic, salt and pepper. Add to bulgur and test for softness. Add extra lemon juice if still slightly grainy. Using food processor, finely chop parsley, mint and scallions. Do not puree. Add to bulgur and stir in diced tomatoes and cucumber. Stir in olive oil and place in bowl. Serve on lettuce leaves. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Buy it from the store.
Put it in the oven. Cook it for 50 minutes at 6°.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients well. Keep in a tightly covered jar. To serve, mix 2 teaspoons mixture in 1 cup boiling water.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken until tender in salt.
Debone and cut up.
Saute onion in small amount of oil until clear.
Add soup, chicken, tomatoes, salt, pepper and cumin.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and fold in sour cream.
Fry tortillas in 1/4 teaspoon cooking oil on medium-high for 1 second on each side, not crispy. Drain on paper towel.
Fill tortilla with chicken and cheese mix.

title: paprika potatoes
directions: Chop onion.
Put about 2 Tbsp. oil in large deep fry pan.
Cook onions in oil until golden.
Take the pan off burner and add one Tbsp. paprika, mixing into onions.
Add potatoes to pan than add the rest of paprika, sprinkling over potatoes.
Add water to just cover potatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are done.
You may have to add a bit more water as the potatoes cook.
There should be some sauce.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of coloring and cocoa; add to first mixture.
Add salt.
Blend in flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Dissolve soda in vinegar and fold in gently.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake in two layer pans.
When cool, split layers to make 4 layers; spread filling between layers.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add grated cheese and tomatoes.
Let simmer.
Add taco sauce to taste.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add peanut butter and cream well. Add vanilla and eggs, beating well.
Add dry ingredients alternating with milk.
Bake in paper cups in moderate oven about 30 minutes.
Frost with sifted confectioners sugar frosting.
(I add 1 or 2 tablespoons peanut butter to frosting.)

title: punch
directions: Mix jello and hot water until jello is dissolved.
Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Freeze in 2 gallon milk jug. Partially thaw before serving so that it is still frozen enough to be mushy.
Mix with 2 bottles of ginger ale, one for each jug.

title: lemon bars
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool.
Mix the rest of ingredients together.
Beat until mixed; add cooled jello.
Bake at 350° in large jelly roll pan for 20 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar mixed with lemon juice.
Pour on warm bars.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine Crisco, cocoa and salt.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix sugar in, in 3 parts.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin if needed.

title: bojangles biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder into a bowl.
Stir in Crisco and milk and mix well.
Form into biscuits or roll out and cut, if desired.
Place biscuits on greased pan and press very flat.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Remove and brush tops with melted butter.
Return to oven and continue baking 10 minutes or until brown.

title: country style pork chops
directions: Coat chops in seasoned flour and brown in oiled skillet. Arrange chops in casserole and place the lemon slices on each chop.
Mix the ketchup, brown sugar and water; pour over chops. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: magic bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Shake in cracker crumbs evenly.
Add milk as evenly as possible.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, nuts and coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: cashew nut loaf
directions: Put nuts, vegesteaks and onion through the food grinder.
Cut part of onion fine and simmer in oil with parsley.
Add savita when onion is done.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into oiled and crumbed bread tins.
Bake, covered, in hot water about 1 hour at 350°.

title: smoked sausage with cabbage, sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Stir chicken broth and mustard in a deep skillet.
Add mustard seed and bring to a boil.
Add sweet potatoes and onions; reduce heat to medium.
Cover and cook about 5 minutes, until potatoes are almost tender.
Add sausage and cabbage.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer, until potatoes are tender and cabbage is crisp-tender. Stir in apple.
Cover and simmer additional 3 minutes until apple is crisp-tender.

title: chicken a la maria
directions: Combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Dip chicken breasts in mixture to coat.
Arrange in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Set remaining crumb mixture aside.

title: mom's chicken cacciatore
directions: Salt and pepper chicken pieces.
Roll chicken in flour and brown in oil.
In small skillet, saute green peppers and onion in a small amount of oil.
Place browned chicken in a deep covered pan.
Add tomato sauce and 16 ounces of water (just fill the empty tomato sauce cans), basil, onion, green peppers and sherry.
Baste sauce over chicken now and then.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine milk, eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla, nutmeg and cornstarch.
Beat well at medium speed until light and fluffy. Add both kinds of corn.
Remember, drain well whole kernel corn. Add melted butter.
Stir well.
Pour mixture into greased pan or dish.
Stir just before putting into oven.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes until slightly browned.
The pudding is done if inserted knife comes out clean.

title: magic coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients
in container of electric mixer and mix on medium speed
for
minute.
Pour	mixture
into buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at	400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish in the oven.
Add flour to butter.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 people.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, Roka Bleu and Cheddar Old English.
Blend together vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Mix together.
Chill and roll in nuts.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg well.
Stir in pineapple.
Blend flour, soda, salt and nutmeg; stir in.
Mix in nuts.
Chill 1 hour. Heat oven to 400°.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 min., or until no imprints remains when touched lightly.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: *Place can of milk in freezer until flaky, about 1 hour.

title: corn tortillas
directions: Combine masa and water.
Mix with hands until dough is moist. Let stand for 15 minutes.
Divide into 12 balls.
Dampen dough with water.
Using a tortilla press or flat baking dish, press a ball of dough with wax paper on each side.
Press until tortilla is 6-inches round.
Peel off top sheet of paper.
Place tortilla on hot, ungreased griddle or skillet.
Gently peel off top sheet wax paper.
Cook for 30 seconds or until edges begin to dry.
Turn; cook until surface appears puffy.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix in milk.
Pour into buttered cake pan.
Add can of fruit.
Put pats of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kitchree(rice and lentils)
directions: Wash rice and dal.
Fry onion until brown.
Combine all the ingredients and add water.
Cook in rice cooker.
When done, mix and serve.

title: pull apart bread
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle bottom with brown sugar and pecans.
Roll thawed bread dough into balls.
Dip into melted butter and roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Drop into pan and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Follow directions on cake box.
Add pistachio pudding mix and almond extract.
Add a few drops of green food coloring.
Put cake mixture in a Bundt cake pan.
Bake according to instructions on cake box.
Add frosting, if desired.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake and cool.
Pour both pineapple and juice on top of cake.
Beat cream cheese with mixer and gradually add milk.
Sprinkle instant pudding on top and beat until thick.
Let mixture set up in refrigerator until of spreading consistency.
Spread on top of cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top of the pudding and top with coconut.
Allow to sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place croutons in well buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine the next 6 ingredients. Pour evenly over croutons and cheese. Sprinkle sausage and optional ingredients over the top. Cover and chill overnight. Preheat oven to 325°. Bake, uncovered, for about 1 hour. Tent with foil if top begins to brown too quickly. Serves 6.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Bring first three ingredients to boil in a heavy pan.
Cook slowly for a few moments (use 1/2 cup sugar).
Mix together gelatin and water.
Pour into hot mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar (other 1/2 cup of sugar).
Fold hot mixture into egg whites gently.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, garnish with whipped cream.

title: shrimp casserole for 12
directions: Prepare shrimp: clean and bring to a boil.
Turn off heat. Let shrimp and water cool.
(May use frozen shrimp.)
Boil the rice until fluffy; add soup, lemon juice, pepper, onion and butter.
Add shrimp and parsley.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Parboil green peppers in 2-quarts water, garlic and salt. Drain and place the peppers on top of shrimp mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Put into 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sonora chicken casserole
directions: Wrap chicken in foil with optional vegetables.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Discard vegetables.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Mix all wet ingredients plus onion.
Tear tortillas into small pieces. Use 2 1/2-quart casserole, using half of each chicken, tortillas, cheese and sauce.
Repeat layering with remaining and ending with the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Freezes well.
To reheat from frozen, heat for 90 minutes at 350°.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain liquid from cans of fruit and dump fruit into a large bowl.
Add chopped up bananas and marshmallows.
Add sour cream and stir well.
Refrigerate approximately 1 hour.
Best served chilled.

title: ann's chicken and rice
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine all liquids including butter.
Place raw rice in bottom of casserole.
Pour 1/2 liquid over rice and mix.
Place chicken on top.
Pour remainder of liquid mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and almonds.
Bake uncovered 3 hours at 275°.

title: sheep-wagon carrot cake
directions: Mix and add to carrot mixture.
Bake in 2 oiled log pans or 1 tube pan at 275° for 2 hours.

title: this 'n that(snack)
directions: Cut the crust off sandwich bread.
Roll each slice flat with rolling pin.
Beat cream cheese, egg and 1/2 cup sugar until well mixed.
Spread mixture on flattened slice of bread and roll up. Dip in melted butter and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Freeze in plastic container.
When ready to serve, slice each frozen roll into 3 pieces (makes about 72).
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sebring's cranberry apple casserole
directions: Put apples and cranberries into a casserole.
In a saucepan, mix butter or margarine, brown sugar, oatmeal and chopped nuts. Sprinkle or spoon this mixture over fruit in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift together cornmeal, whole wheat flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda in a large bowl.
Beat together yogurt, milk, honey and eggs in another bowl.
Place butter in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan and place pan in oven for about 3 minutes, or until butter melts.
Remove from heat; brush butter over side and bottom of pan and pour remaining melted butter into yogurt and egg mixture.
Stir together well and fold into dry mixture.
Do this quickly, with just a few strokes of a wooden spoon or plastic spatula.
It doesn't matter if there are lumps. The important thing is not to overwork the batter.
Pour batter into the warm, greased pan; place in oven and bake 30 minutes or until top is beginning to brown and a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Remove from heat and let cool in pan.
Eat warm or cool, with honey.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Chop in medium pieces.
Melt margarine; mix all together.
Save some cracker crumbs and sprinkle on top.
When mixing ingredients together, use 1 cup of chicken broth.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni or noodles.
Chop beef.
Dilute soup with milk.
Heat and add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add meat, onion and salt.
Combine with macaroni.
Cover with crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger pie with potato fluff topper
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Add drained beans and soup; pour into greased 1/2 qt.
casserole.
Prepare four servings packaged instant mashed potatoes according to package directions, but reserve the milk.
Add egg, and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough reserved milk so potatoes are stiff enough to hold shape.
Spoon in mounds of potatoes over casserole.
Sprinkle potatoes with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grandma's butterscotch brownies
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt chips and margarine; stir until smooth.
Pour mixture into large bowl; stir in sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until well mixed.
Stir in flour, nuts and salt.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.
These pack and ship well to distant grandchildren.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add meat (either poultry or beef). Cover and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed.
While spaghetti is cooking, brown ground beef and onion; add the herb sauce mix, tomato paste, water, margarine and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain spaghetti.
Mix 2 cheeses together.

title: mexican beans
directions: Lightly brown hamburger and chopped onion.
Add all ingredients to pinto beans 1 hour before they are finished cooking.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts for 3 minutes; save broth.
Cut tortillas into bite size squares.
Mix milk and soups to form sauce.

title: freda's stuffin' puffs
directions: Combine water, oil and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Immediately stir in flour.
Let mixture cool 4 to 5 minutes; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mixture should be thick and shiny.
Place on foil on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Cool.
Fill with chilled pudding, cream sauce or stuff with chicken salad, tuna, salmon or other entree.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (first 30 minutes, covered, then the last 30 minutes, uncovered).

title: mom's apple krisp
directions: Mix 2 teaspoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Spread mixture in greased pan.
Sprinkle with water. Blend flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and brown sugar.
Mix in oleo to make crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes or until lightly brown and apples are tender.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Mix celery, onion, margarine and water together.
Bring to a boil.
Mix in croutons and poultry seasoning (can substitute 3 cups Pepperidge Farm dressing mix).
Debone chicken, pound flat and wrap each piece around a large spoonful of dressing.
Place in broiler pan.
Mix together chicken, soup and water.
Pour over chicken. Bake in oven about 1 hour at 350° to 400°.

title: aunt bernice's cookies
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
Roll out when cool. Bake at 375°. Frost and decorate.

title: light and tender pancakes
directions: Measure and mix first four ingredients in 2-quart bowl.
Add milk, egg and oil.
Whisk to blend well.
Drop 1/4 cup amounts onto a hot griddle.
Turn when bubbles begin to break the surface. Serve with fresh fruit or warm maple syrup.
Can be frozen for later use!

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat, celery and onion.
If using stew meat, add some water and cook until tender.
Drain the grease off the hamburger. Add the gravy, mushrooms and bay leaves.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
If too thick, add some water.
Add sour cream right before serving.
Stir well.
Add over cooked rice or noodles.

title: blueberry glaze pie
directions: Crush blueberries and cook with water until almost boiling; continue to mix well.
Sieve.
Stir sugar into blueberry juice. Mix cornstarch with enough cold water to fully dissolve starch; stir until lump free.
Stir starch mixture into berry juice.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Place layer of whole fresh blueberries in baked and cooled pastry shell; coat berries with sauce.
Fill shell about 2/3 way with berries and cover with more sauce.
Fill remainder of pie with berries and cover with sauce, working sauce into spaces around berries.
Chill until firm.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add crushed bananas and mix well.
Sift flour, salt, soda and add to first mixture.
Add nuts. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy haystacks
directions: Microwave morsels 3 minutes.
Stir and heat 30 seconds more. Stir in peanuts and potato sticks.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper and cool.

title: egg and green chili brunch casserole
directions: Drain, seed chilies and cut into strips.
Dry strips on paper towels.
Place chilies in bottom of a 13 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch glass Pyrex dish.
Cover chilies with grated cheese. Drizzle eggs evenly over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool (to finish setting) 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.
Serve with salsa sauce. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: When chicken is cooked, bone, skin and cut in small pieces. Then put back in broth.
Chop celery and a tomato in pieces; put in broth.
Add pepper, salt, garlic and poultry seasoning.
Add noodles.
Add more if you want thick soup.
Cook until noodles are cooked soft.

title: beer and bratwurst
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat until almost boiling.
Simmer, covered, about 5 minutes.
Remove bratwurst and continue simmering onion until tender.
Broil or grill bratwurst 3 to 4 inches from heat about 3 to 5 minutes on each side.
Drain onions and serve.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add chili powder, beans and tomatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Mix well and spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: garlic bagel chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bagel slices on baking sheet. In small bowl, combine oil and garlic.
Brush onto slices. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until crisp and lightly browned.
Yield:
8 to 12 chips.

title: overnight cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion, green pepper.
Layer with salt, celery seed and white pepper.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar and Wesson oil together.
Sift the flour, salt, cinnamon, cloves and soda together and add to the pumpkin mixture.
Add the nuts.
Grease pans lightly.
Place dough in baking pans and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
This recipe makes three average size loaves or five small ones.
When done, turn out on waxed paper directly from oven.
Let cool completely, then wrap in waxed paper and a layer of aluminum foil.

title: chicken primavera
directions: Slice chicken into strips.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Place on grill lined with foil (poke holes for flavor).
While chicken is grilling, melt 3 tablespoons of margarine; season with garlic powder to taste.
When chicken is about done, pour margarine over and let simmer.
Meanwhile, cook noodles and heat sauce.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon sugar in sauce while heating.
Place noodles on plate; top with sauce and chicken.
Great served with steamed broccoli.

title: clam cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
In separate bowl, beat eggs. Add broth and milk.
Add to dry ingredients, blending just until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in clams and drop by spoonfuls into hot fat (365°) and fry until golden, turning once.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill milk in freezer 3 to 4 hours.
Whip in bowl.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Spread crumbs in oblong dish, pour mixture over and top with crumbs.
Freeze until solid or like ice cream.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Put 1 can cream of chicken soup in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Next, layer 6 tortillas (torn in fourths).
Cover with other can of soup.
Add can of boned chicken.
Put another layer of 6 tortillas.
Cover with mushroom soup and other can of chicken.
(I add a little water to thin down the soups.)
Next, layer chopped chili peppers on top and cover with grated cheese. Bake at 375° about 40 minutes.

title: maple icing
directions: Boil maple syrup in small pan until it forms a 3-inch hair. Pour slowly, beating constantly, onto stiffly beaten egg white to which salt has been added.
When cool enough, spread on top of cake.

title: french cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a deep baking dish.
Mix the flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and milk and pour into baking dish.
Spoon pie filling over flour mixture and sprinkle remaining sugar over top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: minced ham and egg spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: green rice
directions: Stir ingredients together and bake 30 minutes at 475°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Boil spinach as directed on package.
Drain off excess water in colander.
Put spinach back into pot on low simmer.
Add Philadelphia cream cheese and butter.
Simmer until butter and cheese melted, stirring constantly.
Add pressed garlic (adjust more or less to taste), salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into casserole dish enough olive oil to coat bottom of dish.
Cut artichoke hearts in half and line bottom of casserole with them.
Pour spinach mixture over artichoke hearts.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs over top.
Bake in oven at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Chop tomatoes, cucumber, onion and green pepper to bite size. Break linguine in half and cook; let cool.
Mix everything in a large bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss thoroughly and serve at room temperature.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Use 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Wash and peel potatoes and slice thing.
Place layer of potatoes in dish.
Mix flour, salt, and pepper together in a dish.
Sprinkle half of flour mixture over potatoes, then place onion slices on top of flour mixture. Place pats of margarine on top of onions then sprinkle cheese on top.
Repeat layers again, starting with potatoes, flour mixture, onion slices, margarine pats, and cheese.
Pour milk into sides until you can see it.
Bake at 400 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Let frozen lemonade thaw.
Using a spoon, mix with whipped topping.
After well mixed, pour into graham cracker crusts.
Top with fresh lemon garnishes and put in refrigerator for 2 hours or until set.

title: sally ann cookies
directions: Mix well.
Chill for 1 hour. Roll out and cut. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Do not brown meat.
Put all ingredients in roaster or crock-pot.
Bake 3 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve over rice.

title: fried peanut butter and banana sandwich
directions: Spread the bread with the peanut butter and banana.
Melt the butter in a skillet on medium heat.
Fry the sandwich, browning on both sides.

title: french vanilla pudding
directions: Grease dish with butter.
Line dish with wafers (save some for top).
Mix margarine, sugar and eggs; pour over wafers.
Whip the whipping cream and sugar.
Pour over other ingredients.
Put strawberries on top of this and place layer of wafers over the strawberries.
Place in freezer.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix Monterey Jack cheese, 1 cup Cheddar, onion, sour cream, parsley, salt and pepper; reserve.
Heat tomato sauce, water, bell pepper, chili powder, oregano, cumin and garlic to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Pour into greased pie plate, 8 or 9 x 1 1/4-inches.
Dip each tortilla into sauce to coat both sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup cheese mix onto each tortilla and roll up.
Arrange in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches.
Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until hot and bubbly.
Garnish with sour cream and sliced olives or lime wedges if desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix first four ingredients together.
Add enough sour cream to hold together.
Let sit overnight, then serve.

title: kahlua fruit dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften to room temperature (about 2 hours).
Combine all of the above ingredients into blender.
Blend on low for about 1 minute.
Pour mixture into bowl; chill for at least 3 hours.
Serve with fruit.
Apples, pineapple, bananas and kiwi are especially tasty.

title: homemade boursin
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Add pepper and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: dorothy doak's apricot casserole
directions: Drain seeded apricots for 1 1/2 hours, then turn cavity up in Pyrex dish and sprinkle with the brown sugar and lemon juice. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Just before baking, sprinkle coarsely crumbled crackers over the apricots.
Drizzle with the melted butter and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 8 minutes.
Add tea, juice of lemons or frozen lemonade juice and ginger ale.
Before serving add juice of oranges or frozen orange juice and pineapple juice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Break eggs into dish with melted butter.
Add sugar, then sift the flour on the sugar and beat together well.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Bake in one crust in moderate oven (325°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
Be careful not to burn, but have it a lovely brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.

title: broiled pineapple-coconut topping
directions: Mix brown sugar, crushed pineapple and butter.
Spread on one baked layer of cake.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and flaked coconut over top; broil until golden brown.
Double recipe for oblong cake.

title: summer squash salad
directions: Thinly slice zucchini and yellow squash.
Combine salad dressing and seasonings.
Pour over squash and olives.
Cover and chill several hours.
Toast almonds.
Cool.
When ready to serve, peel and cube the avocado.
Toss gently with the lemon juice, then add to squash mixture along with tomatoes.
Place on serving dish lined with salad greens.
Garnish with toasted almonds.

title: little pizzas
directions: Grate cheese.
Add bacon; mix in mayonnaise.
Spread small amount on party rye.
Spread out slice on cookie sheet in single layer.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes or until bubbly or lightly browned.

title: dream bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar together and add flour, salt and vanilla.
Spread this mixture in greased pan and bake 15 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Preheat the
oven to 425°.
Roll out half the dough and fit it into
a
9-inch
pie pan.
Roll out the remaining dough and set it aside on waxed paper or a lightly floured surface. Cover with waxed paper to avoid drying out.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed on package.
In a large bowl, combine macaroni with remaining ingredients; toss lightly.
Cover and chill.

title: chocolate oatmeal brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat butter, peanut butter and sugars until creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, cocoa and soda in separate bowl.
Gradually add to peanut butter mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)
Cool for 15 minutes.
Drizzle with vanilla chips, melted over brownies.
You may need to add 1 to 2 tablespoons melted butter to thin vanilla chips.

title: white fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Milnot and margarine together and cook until mixture comes to a boil, stirring frequently.
Boil this mixture for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in Marshmallow Creme.
Add coconut and pecans.
Stir until mixture is creamy and smooth.
Pour into buttered pan.
Allow to cool and cut as desired.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add vanilla.
Sprinkle crumbled crackers over butter and vanilla. Over this spread coconut, then add a layer of chocolate chips and one of butterscotch chips.
Next, sprinkle on nuts.
Finally, drizzle on condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine Italian dressing and water and bring to a boil. Remove from heat; add rice.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes. Cook peas; cool and combine.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients until crumbly.
Press into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Blend well and pour over base.
Bake for 25 minutes longer.
Cut into squares when well cooled.

title: reduced fat chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with Eagle Brand milk and salt. Remove from heat, stir in vanilla, spread evenly into foil lined 8 or 9 inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm. Turn fudge onto cutting board, peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store loosely
covered at room temperature.
Makes about 2 lbs (about 22 servings).
33 % less fat than regular recipe.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a saucepan cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add cheese.

title: cashew chicken
directions: In small saucepan dissolve bouillon in water.
Combine soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and ginger.
Stir into bouillon mixture. Brown chicken in oil in large skillet.
Add bouillon mixture. Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add mushrooms, onions, green pepper and water chestnuts and simmer uncovered 5-8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add 1/4 cup cashews. Serve with rice.
Garnish with remaining 1/4 cup cashews. Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 4.

title: banana nog
directions: Put all ingredients, except nutmeg, into blender with 1 cup ice cubes.
Whip 30 seconds. Pour into tall glasses.
Dust with nutmeg. Serve at once. Makes 2 servings.

title: sweet and sour beets
directions: Drain juice of beets and pineapple into saucepan and bring to a boil.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to mixture to thicken. Pour pineapple and beets into mixture.
Heat and serve.
Serves 15.

title: orange tang pies
directions: Mix ingredients, do not use mixer. Put in 2 graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate to cool.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Follow package directions for pasta.
While pasta is cooking, saute garlic in butter.
Add half and half and pepper, heat until slow boil.
Lower heat and add cheese.
Pour over pasta and mix well.
Sprinkle with green onions.

title: green punch
directions: Mix all but ginger ale; stir well.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: christmas jello salad
directions: Dissolve each Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Drain fruit, reserving liquid separately. Blend cream cheese with enough of the pineapple juice to make it spreading consistency. Add nuts to this mixture and set aside. Add enough water (if needed) to fruit cocktail to make 1 cup. Add this and fruit cocktail to cherry Jell-O. Pour into large salad bowl and put in refrigerator until firm. When firm, spread cream cheese mixture over top and return to refrigerator. Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup. Add this and crushed pineapple to lime Jell-O. Put in refrigerator until slightly set. Then pour lime Jell-O over cream cheese and return to refrigerator.

title: delicious cornbread
directions: Bake in 375° to 400° oven for 30 minutes or a little longer just until done.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger. Brown bacon and onion (brown hamburger separate from bacon). Add browned hamburger, bacon and onion to the other ingredients. Bake in 325° oven for 3 hours. Serves 18 to 20 people. (Is better 2nd day.)

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salted water for about 5 minutes. Melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Add carrot and onion; saute until tender.
Remove from heat and add 1 1/2 cups of cubes, soup and sour cream.
Fold in zucchini gently.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Add remaining cubes (3/4 cup) to butter and toss until coated. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Boil together the butter, water and cocoa.
In a bowl mix together the flour and sugar.
Then add to boiled mixture.
Stir it all together.
Then add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
After all mixed together, pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat slowly, stirring often. Serve with crackers.

title: aunt maggie's pudding
directions: Place water, 1 cup brown sugar and butter in baking pan.
Put on stove and boil 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix together ingredients in blender and refrigerate.

title: blueberry or cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, sugar and vanilla or almond extract. Mix until well blended. Spread this mixture into graham cracker crust. Top with fruit filling (refrigerate). Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Freezes well!

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into loaf and place in greased baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 75 to 90 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut refrigerator sugar cookies into 1/4-inch slices and place on a pizza pan with edges touching.
Bake as directed.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Ice cookie when cooled.
Cut pizza into slices before decorating.
Transfer to serving plate.
Arrange fruit as desired (use blueberries, strawberries, bananas, grapes, mandarin oranges, pineapple, etc.).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese; pour in a 9x13 casserole dish, top with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

title: orange sauce
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thickened; add whipped cream. Especially good with angel food cake.

title: chili corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn bread according to package directions.
Stir in the chilies, cumin, oregano and sage.
Spread in a greased 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In small bowl, stir baking soda into sour cream.
In another bowl, whisk together egg, sugar to taste and the oil, then whisk in the sour cream.
Spray an 8 or 9-inch cast-iron skillet with Pam cooking spray.
Put skillet over medium high heat.
Add the butter and heat until the butter melts and is just starting to sizzle.
Tilt pan to coat bottom and sides.

title: english tea cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugars and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together, alternately with the coffee.
Add raisins and nuts and spread on two greased and floured cookie sheets.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Spread while hot with topping.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: In a small bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and morsels.
Drop by measuring tablespoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl and set aside.
Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in large kettle. Cook until melted over medium heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal, stirring until all pieces are covered.
Spread on cooking sheet until slightly cool.
Put coated cereal into large paper bag with powdered sugar and shake gently until all pieces are coated.
Store in tightly covered dish.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Combine sugar and evaporated milk in a saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Boil 10 minutes over low heat, stirring at all times.

title: potato curry(for those who like it hot and light!)
directions: In a small bowl, combine onion and vinegar.
Cover and place in the refrigerator to marinate for several hours or overnight.

title: easy party punch
directions: Combine juices. Mix and add ginger ale. Pour into chilled punch bowl. Add scoops of sherbet. Serves 20 to 25.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt butter, saute onions and chicken; cook until tender.
Add next 3 ingredients, heat through and add 1 cup sour cream.
In greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan, spread 1/3 cup of sauce evenly. Use 1/4 cup to fill tortilla shells.
Place filled tortillas over sauce in pan.
Pour remaining sauce over rolled tortillas.
Top with cheese and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with olives, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: heavenly hash browns
directions: Dilute soup with water.
Defrost potatoes in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients, except chips.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 12.

title: imitation crabmeat pie
directions: Mix mayonnaise, flour, milk and eggs.
Stir in crabmeat.
Pour into shell and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt butter; add bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over pie.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: french toast
directions: Combine everything except bread in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly. Dip bread so it is covered on both sides.
Fry until brown on both sides.

title: crock pot chicken and dressing
directions: Combine eggs, oil, flour, onion and milk.
Cook as cornbread. Crumble cornbread fine.
Add remaining ingredients and put in large crock pot.
Place 1 stick margarine (cut into pats) on top. Cook on high for 1 hour and low for 2 hours.
Perfect every time!

title: corn casserole
directions: Cut corn from cobs, scraping cobs to remove milk.
Measure 2 cups corn and set aside.
Combine egg yolks with next 6 ingredients in a large bowl and add corn, stirring well.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Fold egg whites into corn mixture.
Spoon into a lightly greased, 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Mix water, sugar and cinnamon sticks together and let come to a boil.
Simmer covered about 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks. Add orange juice, lemonade and cranberry juice.
Refrigerate.

title: candy cake
directions: Mix well about 2 minutes on high speed.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan; pour in 1/2 or more of mixture and have ready 3 teaspoons cinnamon and 1/2 cup crushed candy, such as candy canes or butterfinger or whatever you have on hand.
Add 1/3 cup brown sugar and sprinkle over batter.
Then add balance batter to cover this mixture and bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: delicious chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa well.
Add egg yolks and add milk gradually.
While stirring, add butter.
Cook in double boiler over low heat until thick.
Add vanilla flavoring and pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue using the 2 egg whites.
Bake until brown.

title: crunchy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash. Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter or oleo. Combine squash, onion, sour cream, soup and water chestnuts.

title: brunch eggs
directions: In long oblong shallow dish, layer bread, cheese, optionals, bread, cheese, optionals, until all ingredients are used (2 to 3 layers).

title: buttermilk soup(taratori)
directions: In a mortar mash nuts with salt.
Add garlic and oil; continue to mash to a paste.
Mash in water and vinegar.
Stir mixture into chilled buttermilk or diluted yogurt.
Add chopped cucumber and season with salt and pepper.
Serve cold.
Yields 4 servings.

title: easy oven fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in
shallow
baking
pan in a 400° oven. Dip chicken in fluor, onion salt and pepper mixture.
Place in a single layer, skin
side down, in the pan.
Bake 30 minutes. Turn skin side up
and
bake
until tender, about 30 more minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fix dough as directed on box, let rise for 5 minutes.
Roll in 1/4-inch circle.
Mix cheese, sausage and eggs.
Spread on rolled dough.
Roll and place seam side down on greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Let set for about 5 minutes before cutting.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine eggs, flour, sugar, oil and pumpkin; mix well.
Stir in cranberries.
You may add 1 cup chopped walnuts also.
Put batter into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees.
Cook chicken in large saucepan in boiling water.
Drain, saving the water/broth.
Chop chicken into small pieces.
Add dry spaghetti to boiling chicken water and cook until done.
In another pan, melt butter and saut onion and celery.
Stir in pimento.
Add chicken, soup, milk, velveeta, salt and pepper.
Drain cooked spaghetti and add to chicken mixture. Pour all into a greased, 9x13 in. baking dish.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese on top.
Bake for 35-40 minutes.
Serves 8-10 people.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into cubes.
Flour and season, then fry in oil or grease until brown.
Add onion, bell pepper and mushrooms. Simmer until tender.
Combine milk, soup and tomato sauce in crock-pot; add meat mixture.
Cook all day or night on low heat. Boil rice 20 minutes in 4 cups water.
Pour meat sauce over rice. Can use noodles.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Cut in half and scoop out insides into bowl.
Add butter and rest of ingredients and enough milk to make soggy.
Mash and pour into potato shells.
Top with extra grated cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until cheese melts and potatoes firm.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together except 7-Up.
Add it last; beat well.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: hot artichoke cheese spread
directions: Drain all artichokes well and chop (in food processor if possible).
Place in greased quiche or pie dish.
Spread mayonnaise over top and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Heat oven to 350° and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with chips.
If you like it spicy, use jalapeno tortilla chips or Cheddar cheese with jalapeno.

title: chocolate creams
directions: Mix and roll into small balls.
Place in refrigerator until hard.
Melt 3/4 stick paraffin and large package chocolate chips (semi-sweet) in top of double boiler.
Drop balls in chocolate and let cool on buttered wax paper or cookie sheet.

title: baked rabbit
directions: Coat rabbit with flour and place into baking pan, slice onion and place about.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add garlic powder. Mix 2 soup cans water with soup. Pour over rabbit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tenderness is reached.
Can use crock-pot also.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch and a little sugar together.
Gradually add a little milk to this until well blended and free from lumps. Add this to the beaten egg yolks with salt.
Add remaining milk and sugar.
Mix thoroughly and cook in double boiler until very thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon garlic chicken thighs(makes 4 servings)
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken.
Put chicken in a bowl; toss the thighs with a mixture of the lemon juice, crushed garlic and thyme.
Make sure all sides are coated.
Refrigerate chicken for 2 hours or more; turn pieces at least once.
Place thighs on a rack in baking pan, skin side up.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Half cherry tomatoes.
Add tomatoes.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes to heat through.
Put chicken on serving platter.
Spoon on sauteed tomatoes.
Serve immediately.

title: old english fruit pie
directions: Mix flour and butter or margarine.
Add salt, milk, sugar, baking powder and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites and add to mixture. Place 2 to 3 cups sliced fruit in bottom of deep dish (use peaches, apples, pears and nectarines).
Pour batter over fruit. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with a dollop of ice cream.

title: old time beef stew
directions: Brown beef in skillet with 2 tablespoons hot shortening.
Add 2 cups hot water.
Put in large boiler; add vegetables.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add vanilla, oil and shredded zucchini.
Mix.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts and raisins.
Stir.
Add all the dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan or 3 medium sized loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
You can use mashed bananas instead of shredded zucchini to make banana bread.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased bunt or tube pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Scrape out centers of zucchini, leaving 1/4-inch rim.
Place shell in shallow baking dish.
Coarsely chop zucchini centers, mixing with other ingredients except Ragu and cheese.
Spoon in shells.
Top with Ragu and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: grandma's sour cream cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Beat in eggs.
Combine dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream/milk and mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto very lightly greased cookie tin.
Bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes or until degree of brown desired.

title: microwave toasted nuts
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Place in microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes, stirring twice.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Add condensed milk; beat well. Add lemon juice and beat until smooth. Pour into pie crust and set aside.

title: holiday breakfast souffle
directions: Prepare this dish the night before. Grease 9 x 13 baking/serving dish. Line bottom with bread slices. Spread grated cheese and crumbled meat evenly over bread slices. In mixing bowl, combine eggs, milk, mustard and salt. Pour egg mixture over bread slices. Cover and refrigerate overnight. In the morning, remove cover and bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes or until puffy and lightly browned. Delicious and easy!!! Serves 4 hearty appetites.
