title: gourmet chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend. Measure oatmeal, then put small amounts into blender until it turns to powder.
Blend with flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix together.
Mix together butter and sugar mixture and dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips, grated chocolate and chopped nuts.
Make golf ball size cookies; place inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 55 cookies, approximately.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients; set aside 3 to 4 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Let set in refrigerator a day or two before serving.
Makes a pretty salad for Christmas or anytime.

title: peanut clusters
directions: In a double boiler or in the microwave (on High for 4 minutes), melt chocolate chips and almond bark together. Stir periodically. After well blended, add peanuts 2 cups at a time. Stir until peanuts are well coated. Spoon by teaspoon onto wax paper. After clusters harden, remove and store at room temperature.

title: granola
directions: In a large bowl, combine oats, brown sugar, wheat germ, coconut, nuts, and dry milk.
Add honey, vegetable oil, syrup, coffee, and vanilla.
Stir to coat ingredients well.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, beat well. Add flour and vanilla, beating well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: fool proof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In microwave melt chips and milk until smooth (in mine it is usually about 4 min. depending on the container).
Fold in salt, nuts and vanilla and spread evenly into a wax paper lined 8 by 9 in. pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm - turn out onto a cutting board, peel off the paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and skim milk together in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix vegetables together.
In separate bowl mix sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables and mix.
Refrigerate.

title: lobster tails
directions: Thaw frozen tails.
In a 3-quart saucepan, bring 6 cups of water and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt to a boil.
Add tails.
Simmer, uncovered, for 4 to 8 minutes for 3 ounce tails (6 to 10 minutes for 6 ounce tails; 8 to 12 minutes for 8 ounce tails) or until shell turns bright red and meat is tender.
Drain.
Serve with melted butter and lemon.
(Optional:
black pepper.)

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix corn bread and toast bread with chicken stock.
Add enough so mixture will not be stiff.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Pour into greased casserole.
Bake slowly for 1 hour.
The already cooked chicken from stock can be arranged in corn bread dressing.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Put bread cubes in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan; top with cheese, then sausage.
Beat together the eggs, milk and mustard. Pour over sausage and let set overnight.
Next day, pour mushroom soup and milk over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sacramento fruit bowl
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook water, sugar, lemon juice, anise seed and salt 15 minutes.
Refrigerate until cool. Peel pineapple, melon and cantaloupe and cut into bite size chunks.
Peel and section oranges.
Slice with peel on the nectarines and plums.
Slice grapes in half and remove seeds. Combine in large bowl.
Strain syrup.
Pour over fruit.
Peel and slice kiwi over dish when all other fruits are blended.
Serves 12.

title: ohio buckeyes
directions: Mix ingredients well.
With a spoon, shape little balls and place on wax paper.

title: hamburger supreme
directions: Combine meat, salt and pepper to taste and Worcestershire sauce; mix well and form into patties.
Fry quickly in a little hot fat until brown on both sides; reduce heat to simmer (pour off extra grease).
Mix mushroom soup with milk and pour over patties; continue to simmer until serving time.
(Can be kept hot indefinitely.)
We like it served with rice and a salad.

title: sweet potato delight casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together with mixer.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cauliflower broccoli toss
directions: Remove outer green leaves of cauliflower and break into flowerets; wash thoroughly.
Set aside.
Trim off leaves of broccoli.
Remove stalks; separate into flowerets and wash thoroughly.
Reserve stalks to use in other recipe.
Combine cauliflower and broccoli; add onions.
Toss gently.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well and pour over vegetables, tossing gently.
Cover and chill overnight.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: baked brie
directions: Chill Brie in freezer until firm (not frozen), about 1 hour. With sharp knife, halve cheese horizontally; set aside.

title: codfish cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, shape into patties and coat with flour. Cook until golden on both sides in a fry pan with a little oil.

title: sweet-sour salad dressing
directions: Shake sugar and vinegar together well before adding oil. Shake well again.
Add catsup, Tabasco, chives, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix and let stand overnight before using.
Keep refrigerated.
You may use blender except for chives and garlic.

title: fried potato patties
directions: Mix together.
Add flour until mixture reaches a stiff consistency.
Drop by spoon into hot grease (deep fat).
Turn only once.
Drain on paper towel.
You may add chopped shrimp for "shrimp puffs."

title: richard's baked italian chicken
directions: Rinse chicken breasts; pat dry. Place in shallow baking dish; season with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Cover with Ragu sauce and marinate in refrigerator about 3 hours. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven about 45 to 55 minutes (until tender). Cover with cheese and bake, uncovered, another 15 minutes (until melted and lightly browned). This is so good!

title: apple crumb pie
directions: In a large bowl, toss together sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, allspice and apples until apples are evenly coated.
Spoon into one frozen crust.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare pastry in food processor:
Cut butter into flour; add pinch of salt and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Slowly add egg yolk mixture.
Process 15 to 20 seconds.
Turn onto floured surface and press into a ball.
Knead quickly until smooth.
Chill 20 minutes.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick and fit into pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until golden.
(Or roll out Pillsbury sugar cookie dough and put on pizza pan for sweeter crust.)

title: chicken-n-rice casserole
directions: After chicken is boiled, add rice to broth.
Cook 20 minutes on simmer.
Meanwhile, chop celery and onion.
Saute.
When done, add to cooked rice.
Leave rice on simmer and add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Shred chicken; stir into rice, then add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into casserole dish and top with almonds.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake on ungreased sheet at 350°.

title: cheese cup bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients and fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: spinach noodles with cheese
directions: Saute onions and garlic in margarine until golden.
Stir in cottage cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Cook over low heat until hot.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain immediately and toss noodles with hot cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons of the Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dutch almond cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder, soda and spices.
Add nuts.
Mold into loaf; wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
Slice thin and bake in hot oven (400°) for 8 minutes.
Yields 68 cookies.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems out of mushrooms. Chop up and cook with onions and peppers in butter for 5 minutes.
Stir in bread crumbs and spices. Mix up.
Add 1 teaspoon of butter in baking dish and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Then broil 3 to 4 minutes (not necessary).

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; combine flour and soda.
Add to mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla. Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: mexican chicken(low-fat)
directions: Mix dressing, picante sauce, garlic and chili powder in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Serve warm with flour tortillas.
Great with Spanish Rice and kidney beans. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: brandy slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in the 7 cups water. Steep the tea bags in the 2 cups water for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix all together and freeze. Serve 1 ice cream scoop of slush per glass and fill with 7-Up.

title: best ever gingersnaps
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, salt, soda and spices. Stir lightly. Cut in shortening to resemble coarse crumbs. Stir in molasses and egg. Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll them in the extra sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from baking sheet immediately. Cookies will firm as they cool. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: corn cheese chowder
directions: In the 2 cups of water, steam the veggies, salt and pepper for 10 minutes.
Add creamed corn and continue to cook slowly until veggies are done.
Season to taste and set aside.

title: i don't give a damn dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Prepare cake mix as package directs.
Stir in grated orange peel.
Bake 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in baking dish.
Combine all ingredients. Add mixture and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening together; save 1/2 cup for crumbs.
Add egg, milk and baking soda.
Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 cakes.

title: short cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening; combine beaten egg and milk.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir just to moisten.
Knead gently on a lightly floured surface, about 12 strokes.	Pat or roll to 1/2-inch thick; cut into 9 biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken breasts provolone
directions: In plastic bag, combine 2 tablespoons flour, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Add chicken.
Melt butter in pan and saute chicken until golden and cooked through.
Remove to heated platter.
Cut ham into strips.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes in the same skillet.
Place over chicken.
Stir 2 tablespoons flour into drippings in skillet. Blend well.
Stir in wine.
Gradually add milk until it boils and thickens.
Add cheese until melted.
Serve over chicken.
Serve with rice.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first five ingredients.
Sift together and stir in next four ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° (no higher) for 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape in covered baking dish.
Pour 1 can tomato soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with sour cream. Stir in vanilla and mix well.
Pour half of batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Spread half over batter in pan.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle with rest of the brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix milk, water, eggs and salt into flour.
Pour over piece of beef and then roast.
Serve with gravy.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Mix veggies, chicken and soup in ungreased 9 inch pie plate.
Stir remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes.

title: erbs' spaghetti squash
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter; add mushrooms and garlic and saute for 3 minutes.
Add zucchini pieces and onion; saute 3 minutes more.
Stir in flour until blended; add milk all at once. Cook and stir constantly until mixture bubbles.
Reduce heat to medium-low and cook 1 minute more.
Stir in peppers, then add Ricotta cheese.
Stir until cheese is blended.
Repeat with Swiss and Parmesan cheeses.
Stir in wine if desired.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Using two forks, shred cooked squash; place on two or three individual plates.
Spoon sauce over squash.
Serve immediately. Makes 2 or 3 main dish servings.

title: georgia cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers and put in large mixing bowl.
Mix other ingredients together with crackers.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
This salad keeps well for 4 to 5 days.

title: meatball stew
directions: Blend flour into reserved oil.
Stir in tomatoes and remaining ingredients (except meatballs).
Simmer 10 minutes, adding water if necessary.
Pour over meatballs into crock-pot and cook at least 5 hours.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Cover the bottom of a cake pan with cooked chicken or turkey. Cover with the 8 ounces of cheese.
Mix sour cream with the soup. Spread over the chicken mixture.
Mix the stuffing mix with the margarine. Sprinkle over top and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: thumbprints
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter (medium speed) and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour and salt.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Work with 1/4 dough.
Keep rest refrigerated.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Using thumb, make depression in center of each.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove cookies. Make depression again.
Fill with 1/4 teaspoon jelly.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Cool on wire rack.
Repeat.
Makes 4 dozen.
May freeze for 3 months.

title: alpharetta punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 quarts hot water.
Mix other ingredients except ginger ale.
Suggest using a 1 gallon milk jug.
When ready to serve, mix with ginger ale.

title: scotch-irish shortbread
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar with electric mixer until fluffy.
Sift cornstarch and flour 3 times. By hand, mix small amounts of triple sifted flour mixture to the creamed butter mixture.
Mixture will be stiff.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Poke mixture randomly with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes, then reduce oven heat to 300° and bake additional 10 to 20 minutes until barely golden.
Cut into small squares but do not remove from pan until completely cooled.
Store in airtight container.
Keeps well up to 10 days.
Also freezes well.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix juice, egg, sugar and flour in pan.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring often to prevent sticking on pan.
Cool, then add fruit cocktail.
Beat cream until thick.
Add 1/2 of cream to ingredients.
Top with remaining cream and sliced bananas.

title: brownies
directions: Add flour, baking powder and salt together in a bowl.
In another bowl, cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add carob, all of the other ingredients and mix well.
Spread batter in oiled pan. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool a little and cut in squares.

title: general furniture polish
directions: Mix together.
Rub on furniture with cloth, then buff with chamois for a deep shine.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add tomato soup; blend. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves; add to creamed mixture; blend.
Fold in raisins. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Delicious topped with a cream cheese frosting.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sauce mix and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes until thick.
Stir in sour cream and roast beef.
Heat until meat is hot but do not allow to boil, about 5 minutes. To serve, place 1 cup cooked and drained noodles on each of four plates.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat sauce over the noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sourdough corn bread
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the cornmeal, sugar and salt. Scald milk and add butter.
Let butter melt in hot milk.
Pour liquid over the cornmeal and mix well.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in sourdough starter and beaten egg.
Add soda and cream of tartar. Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan and bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except powdered sugar.
Beat on low speed, scraping bowl often until well mixed, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheets. Bake for 18 to 25 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm and again when cool or shake powdered sugar through a strainer held over cookies.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; add oil, eggs and vanilla. Stir in the apples and nuts.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook, drain and crumble bacon.
Cook ground beef.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Remove any skin and bones from salmon and drain. Mix thoroughly with remaining ingredients except for parsley.
Form into ball and roll in parsley.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or bread sticks.

title: mushroom cheese balls
directions: In a small bowl, beat together cream cheese and margarine until light and fluffy.
Finely chop mushrooms, reserving a few slices for garnish; add chopped mushrooms and chives to cream cheese mixture.
Shape into balls; cover and chill several hours or overnight until firm.
In a small bowl, beat cheese spread with liquid smoke.
Frost cream cheese ball with smoky cheese mixture. Garnish with reserved mushroom slices and fresh parsley.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats, baking soda and cinnamon.
Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugars and beat.
Add the egg and vanilla.
Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin. Drop onto a greased cookie sheet and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Use a 350° oven.

title: hottt! soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain excess grease off. Combine mixed vegetables, tomato sauce, diced tomatoes, diced Ro-Tel tomatoes or diced peppers and Cajun spice. Bring all ingredients to a boil for 10 minutes, then stir and reduce heat for 15 minutes. Get ready for a Hot Spicy Soup-MMM Good!

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and refrigerate for 1 hour or longer.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture, beating well.
Stir in apple and nuts.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cake cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix and beat well the first 6 ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.
Sprinkle 1 box yellow cake mix on top.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks butter and pour over cake mix.
Add desired amount of chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes until crisp and brown.
(Can use two pie pans and bake for 45 minutes.)

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage and cheese at room temperature.
Combine and mix well.
Roll into small balls and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 100 sausage-cheese balls.
May be baked and frozen for later use.

title: onion pie
directions: Melt 1/2 stick oleo in pie pan in a 300° oven for 5 minutes. Pat cracker crumbs into melted butter to form crust.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mash crackers.
Melt marshmallows in cream in double boiler and mix with crackers.
Add cup of cherries, raisins and nuts; blend together.
Pack in graham cracker box and let stand in icebox for 24 hours before serving.
(Line graham cracker box with foil.)

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken or beef and cut into chunks.

Mix with first 4 ingredients and then pour into first pie shell. Turn the other pie shell over the one with the ingredients in it and remove tin shell holder. Cover top of the top shell with egg and cook in a 400° oven until light brown on top.

title: lime salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat juice to boiling point; add lime Jell-O. Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
When Jell-O begins to thicken, add remaining ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in mold and refrigerate.
Serve 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir all except vanilla constantly over medium heat until thick (soft ball stage).
Beat until begins to lose gloss.
Spread on buttered dish.

title: date nut bread
directions: *Vanilla and baking powder right.

title: pretzel salad or dessert
directions: To make crust, mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Cool.

title: holiday pate
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Mix sausage, sweet basil and garlic or onion powder together.
Roll mixture into ball.
Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise a littler at a time until spreadable.
Cover the ball.
Top with paprika

title: cheese patties
directions: Grate cheese and mix with softened butter.
Add flour and salt.
Work with hands until it firms up.

title: irish cream
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Best poured into glass container.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together juice, water, Kool-Aid and sugar.
Blend bananas and 1 cup of juice mixtures.
Mix all together.
Freeze 6 to 7 hours.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season and brown pork chops.
Mix potatoes, soup, milk, cheese, sour cream, French fried onions and seasonings.

title: jacque's soup
directions: Heat oil and butter in a saucepan.
When hot, add the leek and onions and saute for 2 minutes.
Then add the carrots, zucchini, mushrooms and yams.
Mix well and add the water, salt and pepper.

title: veggie sauce
directions: Blend and pour over hot, cooked veggies.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Prepare angel hair pasta as directed on container.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in glass casserole dish adding onion and garlic.
Place shrimp in pan.
Sprinkle shrimp with an even layer of bread crumbs and parsley.
Bake until shrimp is cooked and bread crumbs are golden brown.
When done, spoon shrimp mixture over cooked angel hair pasta.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: tomato-watercress salad
directions: In a shall bowl, whisk the vinegar, mustard and anchovy paste. Whisk in the oil in a thin stream until incorporated.
Season with the salt and pepper.
Place the watercress in a medium bowl and top with the tomato.
Drizzle the dressing over the salad, toss and serve.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Grind and drain green tomatoes.
Cover with cold water and let come to a boil.
Scald 15 minutes and drain again.
Add vinegar, sugar, onions, peppers and salt.
Put spices in cheesecloth and add.
Cook 1/2 hour and seal in hot jars.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan for two hours at 300°.

title: cora's cinnamon pecan coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, vanilla pudding, eggs, oil, water and vanilla together 3 to 4 minutes (medium speed).
Mix together sugar, cinnamon and chopped pecans.
Pat stick of butter entirely around tube pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of sugar mixture around pan so that it sticks to butter.
Pour in half of batter; sprinkle part of sugar mixture on top.
Add remainder of batter; sprinkle remainder of sugar mixture on top.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 40 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix meat, Ro-Tel, tomato paste, cream sauce and beans in a bowl.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with a layer of crushed chips. Spread meat mixture over chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: warm brie stuffed with crabmeat and pistachios(mouthwatering)
directions: Cut Brie in half, crosswise.
Place bottom half, cut side up on serving plate.
Trim and discard crust from top of remaining half. Set aside.
In small bowl, combine pistachios and butter. Microwave on High power for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until pistachios are toasted, stirring after every minute.

title: quick cake mix cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the dry cake mix with oil and eggs until well blended.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan and add sour cream and soup.
Combine with cooked potatoes in crock-pot on low.
Heat for approximately 1 hour.

title: baked salmon
directions: Whisk honey, olive oil and lime juice together in a small bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour mixture over top of fish and marinate for about 35 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: heath toffee bars
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening as in pie crust. Reserve 1 cup of this mixture.
Add beaten egg and buttermilk in which soda has been dissolved and vanilla.
Beat only until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased 12 x 8-inch cake pan.
Top with a cup of reserved mixture, nuts and chopped Heath bars.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Take cream cheese and soften with a little milk.
Mix and make mixture smooth.
Place on bottom of pie plate.
Layer tomato, pepper and onion.
Add taco sauce on top and cover with shredded cheese.
Once you start eating it, you can't stop!
Very good! Dip with taco chips.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: In large greased casserole place layer of noodles, then cheese and corned beef.
Mix soup and milk and add to each layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Stir lemonade and milk until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients. Refrigerate until cold. Serve as a dip with the shrimp.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Place in buttered 1 1/2-quart dish.
Add 1/2 stick of melted butter to broccoli. Cut cheese into small cubes and add to broccoli.
Stir to melt completely.
Crumble crackers and spread evenly over the broccoli. Pour the remaining 1/2 stick of butter over crackers.
Put in 350° oven and bake 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: orange carrot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Fold carrots, mandarin oranges, pineapple and chopped pecans in thickened jello.

title: plantain soup
directions: *Cut finely in pieces.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a large pan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for several hours.
Serve on rice.

title: tea cake cookies(may 15, 1879)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Knead on floured board.
Roll thin.
Cut out.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until brown.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Layer ingredients into 13 x 9-inch baking dish as listed. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix dry ingredients together in a bowl. In a separate bowl, beat eggs, then add milk, oil, honey and vanilla. Beat well. Add dry ingredients and stir.
Add blueberries. Stir just enough to moisten. Do not overmix. Fill greased tins 2/3 full. Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: better than robert redford cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare cake mix according to package directions, pour 1/2 into pan and bake for approximately 20 minutes.
Let cool.
While cake cools in pan, prepare vanilla pudding according to package directions. Cut cream cheese into cubes and drop into pudding.
Mix in using an electric mixer.
Spread pudding/cream cheese mixture over cake. Drain crushed pineapple, spoon over pudding/cream cheese mixture. Top with entire container of whipped topping and spread evenly over cake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
In large casserole, mix mayonnaise, soup, sauteed onion and cheese.
Add broccoli.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour into sheet cake pan. Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350° or until cake tester comes out clean. While cake bakes, prepare the icing.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, beat sugar, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg until creamy. Add flour, oats, baking soda, salt, chocolate chunks and peanuts. Stir until blended.
Drop by rounded tablespoon 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 1 minute before removing from cookies sheet, approximately 2 dozen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick oleo and graham crackers together.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and 2 sticks oleo.
Beat for 10 to 15 minutes until creamy and thick.
You may need to add more sugar.
Place on top of crumbs.
Slice bananas and lay on top of other mixture.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas.
Mix Cool Whip and spread over top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and decorate with cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: snowball sundaes
directions: Put the cereal into the bottom of a large plastic bag.
Use a rolling pin to crush the cereal.
Put the cereal into a mixing bowl.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into tiny balls; bake at 250° for one hour.
Cool slightly and roll in confectioners sugar.
Roll in sugar again about half-hour later.

title: red gravy
directions: Fry seasonings until soft.
Add tomato paste and fry approximately 20 minutes.
Add puree and fry approximately 20 minutes, medium fire.
Put all in pot with water.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Add salt, pepper, bay leaves and bouillon cubes.
Add meatballs, pork roast, pork sausage or any other meats you prefer.
Cook until meats are tender or desired thickness of gravy is reached.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt together marshmallows and 2/3 cup milk.
Let marshmallows cool.
Add whipped cream to marshmallow mixture.
Crush crackers to crumbs.
Put 1/2 crumbs in bottom of loaf pan.
Then put 1/2 marshmallow mixture on crumbs.
Over marshmallows pour 2 cans of cherry pie filling.
Add rest of marshmallows.
Top with rest of crumbs.

title: chocolate or coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa if using.
Add 3/4 cup milk.
Stir constantly over medium heat.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add remaining milk.
Continue stirring until mixture starts to pop bubbles.
Add vanilla and coconut, if using, while still hot.
Tip into baked pie shell.
Use Cool Whip as a topping or make meringue from egg whites with a little sugar.

title: peanut butter filling for easter eggs
directions: Mix together well and shape then dip in chocolate and place on wax paper to set. Makes a large batch.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and spread in bottom of pyrex dish. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Then mix the next three ingredients together and pour over crust after it cools. Put pie filling on top.

title: praline cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cake mix (dry), 1/2 cup coconut, the margarine and 1 egg in a large bowl on low speed until crumbly. Press lightly in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients, beat on medium speed for 30 minutes.
Pour into crust, chill for 1 hour.
Top with whipped topping.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 stick margarine and egg.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 12 to 18 minutes.

title: charles spaghetti
directions: Brown beef.
Pour off grease.
Add chili powder, salt, cream of mushroom soup and tomato soup (rinse soup cans with small amount of water, add to mixture).
Cook until meat is done.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water about 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain. Pour sauce over cooked spaghetti.

title: crazy corn nachos
directions: Put oil in large skillet and saute red pepper, onion and corn until soft.
In bowl, blend sour cream, cream cheese, chili powder, cumin, cayenne, pepper and salt.
Fold into sauteed mixture.
Cover tortilla chips and sprinkle bacon and cheese on top.

title: calico luncheon salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except spinach or lettuce leaves.
Toss well.
Serve on green leaves.
This is still good the second day.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Place each vanilla wafer in cupcake liners.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan when cool.
Chill.
Makes 12.

title: oatmeal pie(tastes like pecan pie; makes enough for 2 pies.)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes in unbaked pie shell.

title: traditional sage cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Melt butter in skillet and saute celery and onions until tender.

title: pork schnitzel
directions: Pound
pork 1/4 to
1/8-inch
thick.
Cut
small
slits around edges to prevent curling.
coat with mixture of 1/4 cup flour, seasoned salt and
pepper.	Combine
egg and milk.	Dip in egg mixture, then in
mixture
of bread crumbs and paprika. In large skillet, cook 3 cutlets at a time in shortening, 2 to 3 minutes on each side.	Remove	from
pan,

warm.
Pour broth into skillet, scraping
to
loosen
drippings.
Blend
1 tablespoon flour and dill
weed
with	sour
cream.
Stir into broth.	Cook and stir until
thick;
do	not boil.
Serve with cutlets.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Combine flour, margarine and nuts.
Spread in a baking dish. Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cool crust.
Spoon blueberry pie filling on top.
Cool.

title: pudding dirt cups
directions: You will also need
8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups, gummy worms and/or frogs (candy).

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together; chill.
Serve with veggies.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix bite size chicken, sour cream, soups, 3/4 package of cheese and chillies together.
Fry tortillas on both sides in lightly greased skillet.
Fill tortillas with filling.
Fold together and place in casserole dish with fold-side down.
If desired, save some filling and spread over tortillas along with rest of cheese.
Add jalapeno peppers to top, according to taste. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.
Remove foil last 5 to 10 minutes to brown.

title: tofu and green beans
directions: Cut tofu into cubes.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Add Tamari and then the tofu cubes.
Brown over medium heat.

title: philadelphia 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well-blended. Add eggs. Mix until blended. Pour into graham cracker pie crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool. Add Comstock cherries if you would like a topping. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: lazy stuffed cabbage
directions: Saute ground chuck and onion soup mix together.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add rice to meat mixture.
Put cabbage in large baking dish.
Spread meat mixture over cabbage.
Mix tomato soup and water together and pour over meat.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: ham delights
directions: Blend butter, mustard and seed.
Add onion and sauce.
Spread open rolls with mixture.
Fill with slices of ham and cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pops chili
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer slowly all day in crock-pot or Teflon pot.

title: salmon log roll
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and chill for 2 hours.
Form in ball or log shape.
Mix the pecans and parsley.
Roll ball/log to cover and chill until firm. Serve with crackers. Serves 12.

title: teresa's jewish apple cake
directions: In another bowl combine all remaining ingredients.
If too thick, add 1 to 2 tablespoons more orange juice.
Grease tube pan. Beginning with batter, layer with apples, batter, apples and end with batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Should have 4 layers batter and 3 layers apples.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in halves, lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash. Combine yolks, crabmeat, celery, green pepper, salad dressing mix and sour cream, blending well.
Stir until well mixed.
Refill egg whites.
Chill until serving time.
Makes 24 stuffed eggs.

title: miniature cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven.
Get bowl, spoons and ingredients.
Grease pan, crack nuts, remove 18 blocks and 7 trucks from kitchen table. Measure 2 cups of flour; remove son's hand from flour.
Wash flour off him.
Measure 1 more cup of flour to replace flour on floor.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: *This requires 4 to 4 1/2 pounds unshelled shrimp.

title: tuna potatoes
directions: Scoop centers from shells.
While hot, toss lightly with ingredients.
Spoon each into shells.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: dump pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix pie filling, pineapple and sugar together.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over all; slice oleo over top.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake 1 hour.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in double boiler.
Pour over popcorn; from into balls.

title: tortilla party tray
directions: Arrange tortilla chips on tray and top with refried beans and cheese.
Microwave on High until cheese melts.
Remove and top with picante sauce and jalapeno peppers.
Serve warm.

title: angel hair chicken casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place chicken and cover with soup.
Salt and pepper.
Cook at 350° until done (approximately 45 minutes). Meanwhile, cook pasta and spinach in chicken bouillon; drain.
Mix cooked chicken with the pasta and spinach; add mushrooms.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: oscar's doggie cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll into 2 (3/4-inch) logs.
Slice off 1/2-inch cookies.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Pop in microwave to warm slightly.
Makes about 30 (1-inch) cookies.

title: basil grilled chicken
directions: Press 3/4 teaspoon of pepper into meaty sides of chicken halves.
Combine melted margarine and 1/4 cup basil; stir well. Brush chicken lightly with this.
Combine rest of ingredients and beat on low speed of electric mixer until well blended and smooth; set aside.

title: brownies
directions: Mix
margarine
and
sugar
thoroughly.
Add
eggs
and vanilla and beat until light
and fluffy.
Sift all dry ingredients into a small bowl.
Take
turns
adding
the sifted dry ingredients and the milk to
the fluffy egg mixture until they have all been added.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased pan (10 x 15 x 11-inch) and
bake
for
30 minutes (or until toothpick comes out clean) at 350°.

title: peanut butter delight(cookies)
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and salt for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray casserole with Pam.
Casserole size is 2 x 8 x 15-inches.
Boil breasts until tender.
Bone and cut in bite-size chunks.
Put 1/2 of dressing in bottom of casserole.
Place chicken chunks on top of dressing.
Add diced onions.
Put 2 cups mushroom soup and 8 ounces sour cream in blender.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with balance of dressing. Dot with butter.
Cook for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in water until tender.
Add salt, pepper, oleo and bouillon cubes to potatoes.
Stir in sour cream and scalded milk.
Add flour to thicken.

title: tomato soup to can
directions: Cook tomatoes, onions and celery until soft.
Strain and heat. Add salt, paprika, sugar and butter.
Boil 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Yields around 20 pints.
Has an excellent flavor. One cup of cornstarch can be added for thickening.

title: microwave apple crisp - dessert
directions: Put apples in 2-quart dish.
Add water to apple slices. Combine oatmeal and dry ingredients and cut in butter.
Put over apples and bake for 15 minutes, turning once in awhile.
Yield: 16.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms, pepper, and celery, then toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well and pour over vegetables.
Chill and let set several hours or overnight.
Mix again once or twice.

title: white christmas cake
directions: Put cherries in colander.
Drain well; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar very well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each one.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour gradually beating with each addition.
Add vanilla.
Put cherries and walnuts into 1/2 cup flour.
Add to mixture.
Include excess flour.
Spoon into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Lower heat to 275°.
Bake for 1 hour or until cake is clean when tested with a toothpick.
Slice thin for best taste.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend sugar, spices and salt.
Add eggs, pumpkin and Carnation milk.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: 100% whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast, sugar and molasses in 1/4 cup warm water. Shake together in a jar and add to the yeast mixture the 2 cups warm water, salt, skim milk powder and oil (optional).
Sift and measure the whole wheat flour.
Add flour gradually, beating until well mixed, using sufficient flour to make a dough stiff enough to handle.
Knead thoroughly on a lightly floured board, keeping dough soft.
Shape into a ball; place in oiled crockery bowl. Turn dough over.
Cover with damp cloth; let rise until double. Punch down; shape into 2 loaves.
Place in lightly oiled pan. Cover with damp cloth; let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: our family chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk.
Cook over medium heat. After it begins to boil, cook for 5 minutes more. Remove from heat. Add the vanilla, peanut butter and oats; mix well. Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Makes 20 to 25 cookies.

title: gala pecan dip
directions: Combine softened cheese and milk, mixing well.
Stir in dried beef, green pepper, onion flakes and pepper.
Fold in sour cream. Spoon into 8-inch pie plate or small baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Saute pecans in salt and butter until crisp.
Sprinkle on top of hot dip.
Serve slightly warm.
Ruffle style potato chips dip best.

title: grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Combine other ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in a baking dish.
Blend the flour, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour batter into the butter.
Pour the peaches over this batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: "sweetish" meatballs and sauce
directions: Meatballs:
Soak bread in water or milk to cover.
When completely soaked, wring liquid from bread.
Add to meat and other ingredients, except brown sugar and ketchup.
Mix well.
Shape into meatballs.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press out crescent rolls into pizza pan.
Bake until golden brown.
Mix the cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise; spread over cooled crust.
Spread on vegetables; sprinkle with cheese. Cut and serve.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Cut dates; sprinkle with baking soda and pour boiling water over that.
Let stand until cool.
Mix other ingredients and add fruit mixture last.
Bake in moderate oven (300° to 350°) for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Dredge roast in this mixture.
Coat Dutch oven with Spry and sear on each side. Reduce heat to 300° and pour this combination over roast:
water, brown sugar, dry mustard, nutmeg and vinegar.
Cook for approximately 3 hours.
Check occasionally with a fork.
When the fork goes in and out with no trouble, that's it.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook Macaroni according to package directions.
Drain Macaroni and add first three cheeses,
margarine, sugar, and mild. Top with shredded cheese and place in oven until top cheese melts.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter or margarine in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle on graham cracker crumbs. Cover with coconut, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in layers.
Drizzle over all condensed milk.
Sprinkle on chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into 64 bars.

title: swiss steak
directions: Remove excess fat from steak and cut meat into 6-inch pieces. Season meat and put it on well floured cutting board.
Cover steak with 1 cup flour; pound with a meat hammer or edge of heavy saucer until 1 cup of flour is taken up.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Pour batter into a loaf pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: smith college fudge
directions: Heat butter milk, sugars and corn syrup to boiling point and boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add chocolate which has been cut in small pieces.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Stir vigorously and when candy changes color, turn into a buttered pan.

title: cholay
directions: Brown the onion in oil until golden-brown.
Add garlic paste, cayenne pepper, cumin powder, tomato sauce, and Cholay Masala. Saut until fragrant then add potatoes and saut another minute. Mix in the chick peas, tamarind paste and lemon juice.
Add a half cup of water and cook covered over low flame for 10-12 minutes. Garnish with chopped green onions, chopped tomatoes, chopped cilantro and green chilies.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: In a deep casserole dish, mix together the Veg-All, water chestnuts, sugar, salad dressing and cheese.
Crush one sleeve Ritz crackers and add 1 stick melted butter.
Put crackers and butter on top of vegetable mix.
Bake at 350° until the cheese is bubbly.

title: heidi's chocolate chips
directions: Cream butter and vanilla.
Add sugar, one-half cup at a time. Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Slowly add dry ingredients and beat well.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Using a food processor, gently process the bell pepper, onion, carrot, and parsley, being careful not to over process. Cut 1/2 of the cabbage into chunks. Place in food processor and process lightly, making sure the cabbage doesn't become mushy. Slice remaining cabbage thinly. Mix cabbage together with processed vegetables. In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients together and allow to stand for a few minutes. Combine mayonnaise mixture with vegetables and toss. Chill for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb dump cake
directions: Put into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread in pan in order given.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pickled sweet peppers
directions: Wash and remove seeds from pepper. Cut into strips. Cook 3 minutes in boiling water. Drain. Bring all ingredients to boiling. Simmer 5 minutes. Pack peppers in jar, cover with pickling mixture. Seal and process in boiling water bath-pints for 10 minutes, quarts for 15 minutes.

title: yellow party cake lemon filling
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons cornstarch and dash of salt in saucepan.
Add 3/4 cup water, 2 beaten egg yolks and 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 teaspoon grated lemon peel and butter or margarine.
Cool.

title: country-style ribs
directions: Cut ribs, put in pan.
Mix ingredients in skillet, cook 5 minutes.
Pour over ribs.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, chocolate, corn syrup and salt in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil and continue to cook until mixture reaches 238° or until a small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, but do not stir.
Cool to 110°, being careful not to disturb pan.
Bottom of pan will feel lukewarm.
Pour mixture into mixing bowl.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture loses its gloss and holds its shape.
Add nuts, if desired and spread into prepared pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: doughnuts
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Beat well eggs in the milk and butter.
Combine mixtures; mix well.
Roll out and cut.
Fry in deep oil at 360°.

title: grandmama jones meat loaf
directions: Beat egg and add 1 cup tomato juice. Add to other ingredients except for
gravy. Mix well and bake 1 hr. at 350 degrees. Add can of gravy to remaining tomato juice and pour over loaf and cook for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour and salt; cut in shortening. Add water, a tablespoon at a time, until dough sticks together. Shape into a ball; divide into 4 pieces.
On floured board, roll 1 piece at a time to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut dough into 1 x 2-inch strips.
Set aside in flat pan until all dough is rolled out and cut.
Heat broth to boiling; drop dumplings in.
Stir; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain.
Mix enchilada sauce with soups and tomatoes.
In a large casserole dish, layer 1/2 the meat, 1/2 the sauce mix, 1/2 chips and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cook at 375° in covered casserole for 25 to 30 minutes. Delicious over salad or can be served alone (casserole is only slightly hot).

title: black bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Soak overnight in water and green pepper, cut in half.
Next day, cook slow, covered, approximately 40 minutes. Saute chopped onion, garlic and green pepper in oil.
Mash approximately 1 cup beans and add to onion mixture.
Put onion mixture in pot with beans.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, bay leaf and sugar.
Cook, uncovered, on medium for 1 hour.
Add vinegar and wine; cook slow for another hour, stirring so it doesn't stick to bottom.
Add olive oil and serve.
Yields approximately 10 servings.

title: magic marshmallow crescent puffs
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip marshmallows in melted margarine; roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Wrap a crescent triangle around each, completely covering marshmallow and squeezing edges of dough tightly to seal.
Dip in margarine; place in muffin pans.
Put on foil and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Immediately remove; drizzle with your own glaze. Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: angel hair primavera
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
In large skillet, over medium heat, saute carrots, squash, zucchini, red pepper, onion and peas in butter for about 5 minutes, until carrots are tender. Add half and half, tomato sauce and herbs.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until sauce thickens.
Drain pasta.
Pour veggie mix over pasta.
Serve immediately.
Takes 10 minutes to prepare.

title: shrimp paste
directions: Let cream cheese soften in a little milk.
Season to taste and mix all together.

title: fudge upside down cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and cocoa.
Mix well.
Alternate adding dry ingredients with milk.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into a greased 8 x 12 pan.
Pour sauce over batter and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
The sauce goes to the bottom while baking and makes a creamy, rich topping.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Combine all ingredients, except spaghetti.
Cook pasta as directed and drain well.
Toss with bacon mixture and serve immediately on warm plate.

title: layer casserole
directions: In bottom of 3-quart baking dish put rice.
Layer with vegetables; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add one 8 ounce can tomato sauce mixed with 1/2 can water.
Add onion and green pepper.
Top with layer of ground beef.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour over 8 ounce can tomato sauce mixed with 1/4 can water.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake covered for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Uncover; bake 30 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin doughnuts
directions: In a medium bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
In a mixing bowl, combine shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir the flour mixture into the sugar mixture.
Then add pumpkin and buttermilk.
Mix well.

title: pumpkin tea bread
directions: Use large bowl.
Beat oil and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add pumpkin and beat well.
Sift flour and spices and add to pumpkin mixture.
Add dates and nuts.
Pour batter into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Line the bottom of pans with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Serve plain or warm with whipped cream.
Freezes well. Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, cocoa and applesauce.
Sprinkle sugar and chocolate chips on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: serendipity beef
directions: Marinate meat ahead of time at room temperature in soy sauce, sugar, starch, salt, m.s.g. and sherry.
In saucepan, cook beans according to directions.
Drain.
Heat oil in wok.
Add the drained meat and stir-fry for a few minutes; add the beans and cook for a few minutes longer.
Serve over hot buttered rice. Serves 2 to 3.

title: corn pudding
directions: Pour corn in casserole dish.
Mix in flour and chopped onion. Pour in scalded milk.
Stir in softened butter.
Mix in beaten egg last.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, then add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add flour mixture.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Press down on greased pans with steak hammer (flour steak hammer).
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 56 big cookies.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs with fork, no mixer.
Melt margarine.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add coconut, buttermilk and beaten eggs.
Add melted margarine last.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken-broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and layer cooked chopped chicken and broccoli. Mix all other and pour over.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Put crumbs over the last 15 minutes.

title: great chicken (slow cooker)
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken in bowl.
Dip each piece of chicken in sauce.
Place piece in slow cooker; pour remaining juice over top.
Cook on low 200° for 6 to 8 hours or high 300° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: italian garden soup(version 2)
directions: Combine all in large pot.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat & simmer 3 minutes. Season to taste with salt & pepper.
Serve with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients together; heat and serve piping hot.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; season with salt, pepper, garlic and chopped onion.
Add chili powder to your taste.
Add meat to sauce and cook slow for 3 hours.
Add kidney beans and cook for another 1/2 hour.
Before serving, sprinkle with shredded sharp Cheddar cheese.

title: denise's ginger ale sunrise
directions: Mix all ingredients into punch bowl and top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make pudding as directed on box, but use only 3 cups cold milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer whole graham crackers and pudding mixture, starting and ending with crackers (3 layers pudding, 4 layers graham crackers, including top layer).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup of the grated cheese.
Combine rest of cheese and all other ingredients except for cracker crumbs; mix well. Coat 2 1/2-quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Place broccoli mixture in dish; sprinkle with cracker crumbs and reserved cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until top is golden brown. Let sit for 5 minutes before serving.
Low-fat; .02 grams fat per 2/3 cup.

title: hershey's kiss cookies
directions: Mix and chill dough in refrigerator at least 1/2 hour.
Roll dough into thinly balls around candy kiss.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool and roll into powdered sugar.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside to fold in later. Cream butter, shortening, and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time and beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture with buttermilk alternately.
Stir in vanilla and coconut.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in three 8 inch greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: yummies
directions: Place crackers on greased cookie sheet with sides.
Bring butter and sugar to a boil; simmer 2 minutes.
Mix in nuts and coconut.
Spread on crackers.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and break into bars.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook meat and onions in a Dutch oven and saute until onions are done.
Add V-8 juice and grated carrots and cook slowly.
Add celery soup anytime after carrots are done.
Add 1 can of water for each can of soup.
Simmer slowly for a while to blend.

title: peanut butter balls(buckeyes)
directions: Mix melted margarine, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Roll into small balls.
Chill.

title: hummus (syrian)
directions: Drain water from chickpeas.
Place peas in bowl.
Add garlic (minced) to peas.
Add lemon juice, salt and sesame seed.
Last, add cumin.
Place mixture in mixer bowl.
Mix for 5 minutes, until well blended.
There's your hummus.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cool.
Remove chicken from bones in small pieces (bite size).
Mix chicken with Ro-Tel and cream of mushroom. In 13 x 9 pan, layer crushed or broken tortilla chips along bottom of pan.
Place chicken mixture on top of chips.
Layer with shredded cheese (enough to cover top).
Place in oven on 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until casserole is bubbly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: beet jelly
directions: To get beet water, wash beets and prepare to steam until skin slips.
Drain beet water and use 3 cups for your jelly.

title: my mom's raisin nut filling
directions: Heat sugar, butter and water plus raisins in skillet and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Add cream until right consistency to spread.
Great to use between layers of cake.

title: beef or chicken flavored rice
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt margarine.
Add rice; stir over high heat until very brown.
Mix chicken or beef bouillon with the 2 cups of warm water; let dissolve.
After browning rice, add bouillon and water.
Cover and cook on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: salmon loaf with shrimp sauce
directions: Drain salmon, saving liquid.
Flake salmon into bowl; add onion, parsley, lemon juice, seasonings and cracker crumbs; mix lightly.
Add salmon liquid plus enough milk to make 1 cup; add eggs and melted butter.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into greased 2-quart loaf pan or casserole.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour or until loaf is set in center.
Spoon shrimp sauce over top.

title: mock sweet breads
directions: Mix and let stand overnight (in refrigerator).
Make into patties; roll in flour and brown.
Place in baking pan.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over patties.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix graham crackers and sugar in bowl.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and peanut butter together.
Add to sugar mixture and put in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Cool.

title: vermouth chicken
directions: Mix together vermouth and lime juice.
Pour over chicken and marinate 1 to 2 hours.
Put chicken pieces into roasting pan. Pour marinade over the chicken.
Cook at 325° until done, about 1 hour.

title: bean salad
directions: Rinse kidney beans with water and drain other beans.
Mix other ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Stir several times.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: In saucepan, blend cocoa, sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk. Cook over medium heat until the mixture comes to a boil and begins to thicken.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Mix 1/4 cup of the mixture with egg whites.
Gradually stir egg white mixture into hot mixture.
Stir in vanilla extract.
Pour in custard cups. Chill.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Add lump of butter and the vanilla. Beat until spreading consistency.

title: orange date cake
directions: Mix this with 1/2 cup flour, then add to the batter.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours in tube cake pan.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Heat juice and pour over jello to dissolve.
Cool.
Add Coca-Cola.
Put in refrigerator until it has thickened slightly.

title: triple chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch pie plate.
In small mixer bowl, beat eggs; blend in sugar and butter.
In separate bowl, stir together flour, cocoa and salt; add to egg mixture, beating until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla extract.

title: microwaved croutons
directions: Place margarine in baking dish (8 x 8-inches).
Microwave uncovered on High (100%) until melted, 15 to 30 seconds.
Stir in parsley flakes, salt and paprika.
Add bread cubes and mix to coat.
Microwave uncovered on High (100%), stirring every minute until golden brown and crisp, 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes.
Let cool.

title: corn relish
directions: In microwave, heat vinegar, sugar and oil until sugar dissolves.
Drain and mix peas, Shoepeg corn, Mexican corn, olives, onions, celery, pimientos and mushrooms.
Mix in vinegar dressing and store in refrigerator until well chilled.
Will keep for up to 2 weeks.
Goes well with everything.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into chunks in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar, milk, salt and pepper
together and pour over cabbage.
Lay 6 slices of bacon over the top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover for the last 10 minutes.

title: turkey chili wraps
directions: Brown turkey and vegetables in hot oil.
Add and mix tomato sauce and pepper sauce in skillet.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Spoon about a cup of filling into the center of tortilla. Fold sides and roll from bottom up.
Cut in half and serve.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes. Mix meal, flour, salt and pepper in shallow pan or plate.
Coat each slice of tomato with meal mixture.
Fry in medium hot oil.
Turn and brown other side.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Salt and pepper roast; brown under broiler in roaster pan. After well browned, add water mixed with bouillon cubes.
Combine all other ingredients and put on roast (350°).
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes per pound.
Remove; let cool slightly before slicing very thin.
Return to au jus sauce in roaster.
Serve on French or Vienna bread.

title: baked cabbage and cheese
directions: Cook
cabbage until tender in small
amount
of
salted water. Drain and put in buttered baking dish.
Make
a
white sauce of the butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese
to sauce and pour over cabbage.
Cover with crumbs and bake at
350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: hot mustard
directions: Combine all the ingredients and beat well until smooth and creamy.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cook at medium-high, stirring constantly, until it reaches a pudding consistency.
Cool and keep refrigerated.
Small jars are excellent for storing.

title: chocolate chip
directions: Melt chips in oleo and pour into confectioners sugar.
Add the vanilla and sweet milk. Spread.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease baking dish.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and mix until crumbly.
Dice apples and put into baking dish.
Pour mixture over apples and drizzle on the butter. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt butterscotch, butter and peanut butter together over low heat until creamy.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and walnuts; mix together.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: fruit-nut bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and milk, stirring until mixture is well moistened and crumbly.
Reserving 1 cup mixture, press remaining into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread with mincemeat.
Sprinkle evenly with remaining mixture and nuts.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Stirring constantly, cook onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic in butter until tender.
Add tomato sauce, shrimp, parsley and other seasonings.
Cover and cook slowly about 20 minutes or until shrimp are tender.
(If too thick, add water.
If not thick enough, mix a heaping teaspoonful of flour and 1/4 cup of water and pour into mixture, stirring constantly.)
Serve over rice.

title: chinese beef and rice
directions: Cook beef until tender, put beef and all vegetables in skillet with oil.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Cook until thickened.
Cook rice as directed. Pour meat mixture over rice.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Grind sausage, cheese and eggs.
Add soup.
Mix well.
Place on open face bun and broil until heated.

title: pistachio cheese cake
directions: Layer 1:
Melt
margarine.
Add flour and 1/2 cup nuts. Blend. Spread in
x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken and chestnuts
directions: Melt butter and add flour, salt, garlic salt and chicken to frying pan.
Cook for about 2 minutes, until tender.
Add soup, milk and remaining ingredients.
Heat all together.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cukes in sour cream
directions: Slice cukes thin.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Rinse and squeeze cukes.
Put into sauce.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix until moistened.
Pour in greased muffin pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine jalapeno cheese dip and the bean dip; spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine sour cream and taco mix; spread on top of the jalapeno cheese and bean dip mix. Chop tomatoes and spring onions.
Drain olives; sprinkle over first 2 layers, then layer the rest of the ingredients as follows: tomatoes, onions and shredded cheese.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: lee's favorite brownies
directions: Microwave butter, sugar and water on High until mixture bubbles (5 to 6 minutes).
Add chocolate; stir until melted and smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring well after each.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir completely. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: upside-down ham loaf(serves 10)
directions: Melt butter in 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Add brown sugar.
Cook until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly.
Arrange pineapple in pan.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Combine ham, pork, bread crumbs, pepper, eggs and milk in bowl; mix well.
Spread over pineapple; press down.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Invert onto serving plate.
Serve with whipped cream, flavored with horseradish to taste.

title: sliced baked apples(great fall dessert!)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Peel and core apples, leaving them whole.
Slice apples horizontally into 1/4-inch slices. Reassemble slices to form whole apple shapes and brush apples with lemon juice.
Put apples in a pie plate.
Fill center with some brown sugar, butter and rum.
Bake apples, basting frequently, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Insert cinnamon sticks in center and bake apples, basting frequently, for about 25 minutes until they are tender, browned well and juices are thick and syrupy.

title: top of stove pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together and cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into 8-inch baked crust.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: In
saucepan

combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. Gradually stir in milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens. Cook for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks; return to hot mixture. Cook for 2 minutes more, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in butter. Layer crackers, bananas and pudding mix in casserole dish. Top with Meringue.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, white sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: blushing apple cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well. Add apples and stir to mix.
Pour into pie crust.
Roll out dough to fit top.
Cut slits.
Seal and flute edges.
Bake 50 minutes until golden and apples are tender.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Press meat mixture in ungreased 8 x 4-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until meat is well browned and firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water together until hard ball forms in water.
Add peanuts.
Cook until they pop and syrup turns amber. Remove from fire. Add soda, beat and pour on buttered cookie sheet.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter, egg yolks, brown sugar and 1/4 cup granulated sugar, salt, flavor and spices.
Stir in milk and mix well.
Beat egg whites, at room temperature, at high speed of electric mixer for about 1 minute.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, a little at a time, until whites form stiff peaks.
Fold egg whites into sweet potato mixture.
Pour into pastry shell (unbaked).
Bake at 410° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for an additional 45 minutes or until set.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain; reserve 1 1/2 cups liquid. Season with salt and pepper.
Mash.
Combine reserved liquid and remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup stuffing mix.
Stir in squash.
Top with reserved stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruit; combine with apples and grapes.
In separate bowl, mix softened cream cheese, sugar and sour cream. Pour over fruit.
Add pecans and marshmallows; mix well. Refrigerate.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain juice from pears.
Save juice and bring it to a boil. Add to Jell-O, stir well.
Chill until partially set.
With mixer, beat pears and cream cheese until well blended.
Add partially set Jell-O and pecans to cheese and pear mixture.
Stir well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill for several hours.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Combine broth with salt to taste in 3 to 4-quart saucepan, over medium-high heat.
Add potatoes, celery and leeks.
Reduce heat to medium, cover and cook until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.
Puree vegetables in batches with some liquid in processor or blender.
Return puree to saucepan, blending well. Place over medium heat.
Add butter, stirring until melted.
Ladle into bowls.
Top each with sour cream and chives.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray baking dish (13-inch) with oil cooking spray.
Boil chicken breasts until done.
Remove from water to cool; shred chicken.
Add can of diced tomatoes (drained), green chilies (drained) and green onions to chicken. Put 2 tablespoons of chicken mixture in tortilla and roll.
Place rolled tortilla, seam down, in baking dish.
Pour green enchilada sauce over rolled tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until heated through and cheese has melted.
Serve with rice.

title: bacon and cheddar bubble bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray 8-inch pan. Separate dough into 8 rolls. Cut each roll into quarters.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Peel, core and very thinly slice apples. Melt 2 tablespoons butter over medium-low heat in a small frypan. Saute apples until just tender, about 3 minutes.
Keep warm while preparing batter.
Place a 9 or 10-inch cast-iron or ovenproof pan in oven to heat for at least 5 minutes.
The pan has to be very hot.

title: sesame broccoli
directions: Steam broccoli until slightly tender, but still crisp. Set aside. In a small saucepan combine oil, soy sauce, sugar and vinegar, stirring constantly. Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved. Place broccoli in a serving bowl. Drizzle with sauce mixture and sprinkle with sesame seeds.

title: hoecakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well except for frying oil. Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat. Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot skillet. Use approximately 2 tablespoons batter per hoecake. Brown until crisp. Turn and brown on other side. Drain on paper towels. Leftover batter will keep in refrigerator for up to 2 days.

title: herb's seasoning blend
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Use in omelets and to season fish, vegetables or chicken.
Makes 1/4 cup.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Place
in casserole dish and top with remaining tube of Ritz crackers.
Drizzle with butter and heat in oven thoroughly.
May be halved.

title: taco salad pasta
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: tony's favorite tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles with salt until tender; drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise and vegetables in a large casserole dish.
In saucepan, blend soup and milk, adding cheese slowly to make nice thick sauce.
Add to tuna mixture, stirring until completely mixed. Bake in hot oven at 425° for about 20 minutes or until bubbling. (This is very high in calories, but very tasty!)

title: catfish parmesan
directions: Dip catfish in combined milk and egg.
Combine cheese, flour and seasoning.
Cover fillets with cheese mixture.
Spray baking dish.
Pour margarine over catfish and bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: pocatello potato cake
directions: In a small saucepan, heat milk to simmer; add chocolate.
Stir until melted.
Stir milk mixture into mashed potatoes.
Cool.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple, then add Cool Whip, then orange mandarins.
Chill and eat.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Crumble potato chips on top.

title: rocky road clusters
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a 2-quart glass measuring pitcher. Stir in milk and add butter.
Cook uncovered in microwave oven 4 minutes at High; or until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir well. Continue cooking 1 minute on High.

title: cheese and jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix basic cornbread dry ingredients according to recipe.
Add cheese, jalapenos and onions to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add wet ingredients.
Stir well.
Mixture will be thick and chunky. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Arrange apples in greased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. In small saucepan mix brown sugar, 1/4 cup of the flour, the spices and 1/4 teaspoon of the salt.
Stir in water.
Place over low heat.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Stir in a tablespoon of the butter and lemon juice.
Pour over apples.
Mix remaining flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in seasonings and butter until particles are like corn meal.
With fork, stir in enough milk to make soft dough.
Spoon onto apples, making 8 biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until biscuits are browned and apples are tender.
Serve warm or cool with any desired topping or sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and let stand 2 hours.
Make a syrup of the remaining ingredients.
Boil until dissolved, then cool. Drain cucumbers and pour syrup over; mix well.
Pack in containers and freeze.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Melt margarine and oil in baking pan.
Cool slightly.
In a paper bag, shake chicken in seasoned flour until coated.
Roll pieces in oil in baking pan and arrange so they do not touch. Sprinkle with lemon juice and half the sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Turn chicken; sprinkle with remaining sesame seed and minced onion.
Cook for 30 minutes, basting occasionally, until done.
Serves 6.
Per Serving:
310 calories.
Exchanges:
3 lean meat; 2 fat.

title: corn moussaka
directions: Spread corn in ungreased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Brown ground beef. Drain off excess fat. Add flour and cook 1 minute. Stir in tomato sauce, garlic salt and cinnamon. Pour over corn in dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Shred lettuce and chop tomatoes. Can use other favorite salad ingredients of your choice. Brown ground beef with onion; drain meat and let cool slightly. Toss all ingredients together just before serving. (Fritos will be soggy after a short time.)

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Mix salt, cocoa, baking powder and flour together.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add half of the flour mixture and half of the milk, then the other half of each; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Make jello. Add ingredients.
Mix together and put in a large mold.
Great for Thanksgiving.

title: mexacali bows
directions: To serve at room temperature, combine ingredients in a large bowl and serve.
To serve hot, combine salsa, beans and corn in a large skillet.
Heat through.
Toss with hot bows and serve.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Add pineapple and bring to boil.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Cool!
Add cottage cheese, cream and nuts.
Mix well and put in refrigerator until set.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: In a large quart pan, combine onions, garlic and one cup of broth.
Bring to a boil over high heat, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until liquid and vegetables start to brown, about 10 minutes.
To deglaze, add 3 tablespoons water and stir to loosen browned bits.
Cook until liquid evaporates and mixture begins to brown again, about 1 minute.
Repeat deglazing step about 3 times more or until mixture is richly browned.
Cut up sausage in quarter slices and stir in adding 1/2 cup more water.
Cook, stirring gently, until liquid evaporates and meat begins to brown, about 10 minutes.
Add remaining 4 cups of broth, stir to loosen browned bits.
Cut up tomatoes and then add with liquid to pot.
Add wine, basil, sugar, bell pepper, zucchini and pasta.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until pasta is tender to bite, about 15 minutes.
Put into serving bowl, sprinkle with parsley and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: yorkshire devils
directions: In a small mixing bowl, mix together deviled ham, bread crumbs, sage and scallions.
