Roll into 12 even size balls (about 1 teaspoon to 1 1/2 teaspoons each).
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the flour and salt.
Make a well in center and break egg into it. Gradually beat in the milk, keeping smooth.
Batter will be thin. Put 1/4 teaspoon oil in each of 12 muffin pan cups (1/3 cup capacity).
Then add a ball of deviled ham mixture to each.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 2 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour some batter over each ball.
Bake in 425° oven until browned and somewhat puffed, about 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: terrific french toast
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add orange juice, Grand Marnier, milk, sugar, vanilla, salt and peel and mix well.
Dip bread into egg mixture, turning to coat all surfaces.
Transfer to baking dish in single layer.
Pour any remaining egg mixture over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally (liquid will be absorbed).
Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat. Add bread slices in batches and cook until browned, about 8 minutes.
Turn and continue cooking until browned.
Cut bread diagonally.
Arrange on platter and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve immediately.
Pass butter and maple syrup.

title: diet buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple in juice to boil, remove from heat and dissolve jello in hot pineapple and mix well. Add buttermilk and place in refrigerator to congeal. If large salad is desired, double this recipe. Bananas may be added. Also low fat whipped cream.

title: beef and pork
directions: *If you do not have Ritz crackers, you can use cornbread or toast.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Place broccoli in shallow buttered baking dish.
Blend soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gingerbread bars(good for packing picnics and on hikes)
directions: Blend oleo, sugar, molasses, water and vinegar.
Add dry ingredients.
Press dough into a greased 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes, until it has puffed up and fallen back down.
Cool and cut into bars.
They're chewy, don't crumble and keep their flavor, probably because there's no egg.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Oil 8-inch square pan.
Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve plain or add yogurt or ice cream or whipped cream.

title: yellow bird drink from sonesta beach bar at nassau
directions: Mix all together and garnish with a slice of lemon or lime.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa. Add eggs and beat. Add milk, vanilla and oleo. Add coconut and nuts. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: butternut souffle
directions: Combine squash and butter; mix well.
Add sugar or honey, milk, salt and other spices; mix thoroughly.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry cranberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients but margarine and place in an unbaked pie crust.
Drop margarine on top.
Put top
crust on and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: ham pie
directions: Saute onions in margarine in 1 1/2-quart pan on stove.
Use a whisk and stir in flour; makes a paste.
Add broth and milk and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add ham.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Mix dough and roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and arrange on top of ham mixture.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: chickenetti
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put in casserole dish. Top with browned bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: stove top stuffing squash
directions: Cook (boil) squash and onions for 5 minutes.
Combine soup and sour cream; fold into squash and onion mixture.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing as for dry.
Spread 1/2 Stove Top on bottom of a 9 x 9 or 12 x 7-inch pan.
Pour squash mixture on top of stuffing; then sprinkle rest of stuffing on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ritzy chicken
directions: Crush 1 stack crackers.
Mix with 1 stick melted margarine. Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chicken over crumbs. Combine chicken broth, soup and sour cream in a bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Top with layer of other stack crushed crackers.
Melt other stick of margarine.
Pour on top layer of crackers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cover pan with foil for the first 15 minutes.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Fry meat and onion in butter; add peppers and celery.
Cook until tender.
Then add tomatoes.
Boil noodles according to instructions on package.
Drain and add to mixture.
Put in a baking dish; dot with butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Place in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread undiluted soup over bottom of 4 to 5-quart rectangular baking dish.
Add chicken and turn to coat. Sprinkle with thyme.
Add sweet potato chunks, cover and bake 50 minutes.
Stir in peas, cover and bake 10 more minutes or until chicken is done.

title: panhellenic lemon squares
directions: Mix together like making pie crust the butter, powdered sugar and flour.
Press mixture lightly into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake in 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes.

title: party cheese cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until creamy.
Add next 2 ingredients. Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Blend well after each addition (the more you beat the better it is).
Bake in a greased and floured spring-form pan.
Place pan in another pan with 1-inch or more of water.
Don't let water evaporate.
Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours.
Serve cold; don't release spring-form pan until ready to eat.
This cake freezes very well.
Yum-yum!

title: chocolate chip blonde brownies
directions: Measure flour; add baking powder, soda and salt; sift again. Add chopped nuts; mix well and set aside.
Melt butter or other shortening in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
(If vegetable shortening is used, add 1 tablespoon hot water; cool.)
Add slightly beaten egg and vanilla.
Then add flour mixture, a small amount at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 package Baker's semi-sweet chocolate chips over top.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake. Cool in pan and then cut into bars.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Place first 3 ingredients above in a 2-quart microwavable container. Cook in microwave on High for 4 minutes. Take out and stir. Place back in microwave for 4 minutes. Take out and add butter and vanilla. Place back in microwave for 2 minutes. Remove and add baking soda and swish. Pour on greased cookie sheet and let cool. Break up into pieces.

title: grandma mehring's drop sand tart cookies
directions: Mix and drop small amounts from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Dip fork in beaten egg and press down on cookie. Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad ring
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Refrigerate until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Add ground fruits, nuts and pineapple.
Pour into a lightly greased 10-cup mold.
Chill until firm or overnight.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
Fill center with mayonnaise.
Garnish with orange slices, if desired.

title: chicken liver appetizers
directions: Cut livers in half.
Leave mushrooms whole.
Brown in margarine or butter.
Add garlic, parsley and pepper.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add wine and cook on low in skillet, about 5 minutes, or until livers are no longer red inside.
Transfer to chafing dish to keep warm.
Whole small button mushrooms can be used instead of straw.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Cook onion and butter or margarine in large frypan 10 minutes. Add chili, corn and tomatoes; mix until well-blended.
Pour into 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to box directions.
Stir cheese into dough.
Spoon dough around edge of baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: good oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Fold in cream mixture.
Stir in oats.
Roll in small balls and place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix sugar, milk, syrup and salt in iron skillet and cook until it reaches soft-ball stage. Remove from heat. Add butter, vanilla and walnut pieces. Beat constantly until it begins to get thick. Pour at once on a buttered platter and mark into squares.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix butter and garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.
(These taste just like the ones they serve at "Red Lobster.")

title: pralines
directions: Mix together sugar, syrup and cream.
Bring to a boil.
Let boil to the soft ball stage.
Let cool some.
Then beat and add pecans.
Beat until it begins to lose its gloss.
Pour into individual pralines on waxed paper.
Let cool and then eat.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Heat margarine, cocoa and milk over low heat.
Do not boil. Remove from heat; stir in sugar and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.

title: apricot liqueur
directions: In a 3-quart stainless steel or enamel saucepan, stir together the apricots and water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cover and bring to a boil over medium heat and boil gently 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar until dissolved.
Stir in vodka, corn syrup and brandy until well blended.
Cool to room temperature, stirring occasionally.
Pour fruit and liquid into large, glass container; loosely cover.
Let stand at room temperature at least a week. Drain liquid from apricots; reserve.
In a strainer, place over a bowl, put apricots one layer at a time.
Gently press with back of spoon to extract as much liquid as possible.
Reserve apricots. Mix reserved liquid and apricot nectar; strain through four layers of damp cotton cheesecloth.
Store in tightly covered glass container in refrigerator.
Makes about 6 cups.
To make brandied apricots, heat and serve the reserved apricots as a garnish for meats and poultry.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Coat 2 1/2 quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
In large skillet, brown ground beef. Remove from heat.
Drain any excess liquid.
Add onion, garlic powder, taco seasoning and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
In medium bowl, combine sour cream and cottage cheese.
Place half the crushed chips in bottom of prepared casserole dish.
Add enough meat mixture to cover chips, then cover meat with half the sour cream mixture and sprinkle with half the shredded cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in preheated oven 30 to 35 minutes until cheese melts and casserole is heated through.

title: red cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage and place in large bowl.
Combine vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Add to cabbage mix.
Place in refrigerator and allow to marinate 1 hour before serving.
Serves 4.

title: corn pudding(ada hill's recipe)
directions: Grease a 1-quart casserole.
Beat sugar and eggs.
Add milk, mixing well.
Add corn and bread crumbs, mixing well.
Add nutmeg, mixing well.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg; dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and set aside. Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda and nuts.
Mix with cocoa mixture, stirring well.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs and sour cream until smooth. Add to flour mixture.
Bake in a large, well-greased sheet pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Punch holes in cake with a toothpick and pour icing over cake.

title: old spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator. May need to add more dressing, the cheese soaks it up.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice, lemon juice and water.
Bring liquids to boil and add Jell-O and cool.
Break up cranberries and add them and nuts to mixture.
Mix well.
Add celery and pineapple. Refrigerate to congeal.

title: spinach balls a la liz
directions: Cook frozen spinach as directed.
Drain.
Squeeze spinach by hand to remove all moisture.
This takes a long time.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly with hands.
Refrigerate about 3 hours or overnight.
Roll into balls, using rounded teaspoonful per ball. Leave plain or at this point, you may roll balls in a bowl filled with about 2 cups grated Parmesan cheese.
Place on cookie sheets and bake for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
This bakes LOTS of spinach balls but never fear, they will quickly disappear.
Your guests will love them!

title: low calorie cabbage
directions: Place beef bones in large pot with water to cover.
Let them boil with some of the same seasoning until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Put meat in pot with stock from meat, about 2 cups of more.
Add the cabbage and more seasoning, if needed.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes.
Very good with hot water cornbread with jalapeno peppers.

title: hope pies
directions: Drain peaches and save 1/3 cup syrup.
Place peaches in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with 4 tablespoons sugar and orange rind.
Heat in oven while preparing batter.
Sift flour once; measure.
Add salt and baking powder and sift again.
Work in margarine.
Add beaten egg and peach syrup.

title: potato soup
directions: Grate or dice fine; add to 1 can chicken broth.
Season to taste.
Add water to cover and cook until done.
Add 1 stick of butter and let melt.
Add 1/2 pint whipping cream and 1 pint half and half cream.
Heat and serve (very velvety smooth).

title: red velvet cake
directions: Using a fork, blend together the food coloring and instant cocoa.
Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Stir in coloring mixture.
Beat in buttermilk.
Add flour and salt, which have been sifted together. Stir in (do not beat) vinegar, then vanilla.
Fold in soda.
Pour into 2 waxed paper lined 8-inch cake pans, which have been greased on the bottoms only.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Can use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dirt cake
directions: Use a two-quart flower pot.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil macaroni; mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and cook noodles until soft.
Add cottage cheese and spaghetti to meat.
Place 5 noodles on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread half of sauce mix over noodles and top with 6 slices of cheese.
Add remaining noodles, another layer of sauce and top with cheese.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes or until cheese starts to brown.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes. Chunk Velveeta and add.
Microwave until cheese melted.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Beat egg, add sugar and beat until thick and light yellow in color.
Stir in milk.
Add enough clean snow (gathered from tops of cars or low roofs, etc.) to thicken.
Add flavorings.
Serve at once.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1 cup of pecans.
Make into a ball and roll in 1 cup of pecans.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve at room temperature.

title: lemon curd - microwave(fills 20 small tarts)
directions: Beat eggs in a 4-cup glass measuring cup.
When smooth, add other ingredients with a wooden spoon.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes on low, stirring every 2 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cut up chicken into strips, chop onion and place in a 9 inch by 11 inch pan.
Pour water over, cover with foil and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven add butter rice and cream of chicken soup, bake an additional 30 minutes.
Cool for a few minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter rice krispie bars
directions: Bring to a boil (4 minutes on High in microwave) the sugar and corn syrup.
Stir until melted, then add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add with difficulty Rice Krispies.
Press lightly into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt in a glass bowl on High in microwave for 2 minutes the peanut butter chips and chocolate chips.
Pour over Rice Krispies mixture and spread.

title: red cajun bean soup
directions: Cook beans in salt pork and salted water for approximately 45 minutes.
Add all ingredients except sausage.
Cook 1 hour; add sausage and cook 45 minutes or longer.
This is a hot receipt.

title: lemon-pineapple dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let stand in refrigerator until "half set," then whip.
Add pineapple; fold in whipped cream. Refrigerate until firm.

title: queen's biscuits(biscotti di regina)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 baking sheets.
Sift first 4 ingredients into large bowl.
Cut shortening in with pastry blender until size of peas.
Stir in eggs and one tablespoon milk at a time to make a soft dough.
Mix thoroughly.
Break into small pieces, roll between palms to form rolls about 1 1/2-inch long. Flatten slightly, roll in sesame seed.
Place on cookie sheet about 3/4-inch apart.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool on rack.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and
drain
off fat.	Chop/dice green pepper, tomato and onion.
Tear
lettuce into bite-size pieces and place in large bowl.
Add
diced
veggies, ground beef and Catalina dressing.	Crush Doritos
and
add to mixture.
Blend well and serve.

title: lime applesauce ginger ale jello
directions: Heat applesauce.
Add Jell-O; mix well.
Put in bowl while warm and add ginger ale.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add to mixture and mix well.
Then add to cooled oats and mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for about 45 minutes.

title: rolled dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk and oil.
Flour counter and top of dough before rolling.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into dumplings approximately 1 1/2-inch by 1 1/2-inch.
Dry slightly for easier handling.
Drop into boiling broth and chicken.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Yields 4 large servings or 6 reasonable servings (9 grams of fat each).

title: fried chicken livers
directions: Wash livers, removing all membrane; set aside.
Mix flour, salt and pepper in a bowl or small poke (brown paper bag).
Heat 1/4-inch of oil, grease or lard in skillet until a couple of drops of water sizzle.
Coat livers with flour mixture and place in skillet (don't crowd).
Fry 10 minutes per side, until brown.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking soda, eggs and pineapple.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blender hollandaise sauce
directions: Warm blender with hot water. Place egg yolks in blender with lemon juice
and
salt.
Cover
and
set
blender on high speed for 3
seconds.
Remove cover and add melted butter in a steady stream while blender is on high speed; turn blender off as soon as all of the butter has been added.
Yields 1 cup.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and bell pepper.
Drain off excess fat.
Add all other ingredients to hamburger mixture.
Mix well and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla. Slowly pour in hot milk. Pour at once into pie shell.
Bake in very hot oven at 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 minutes longer or until knife comes out clean.

title: one dish meal
directions: Place in large baking dish in order given.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: frozen salad(serves 21)
directions: Mix Philadelphia cream cheese and salad dressing together. Add whipped cream, pineapple and marshmallows.
Freeze and serve.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Into glass bowl, layer the lettuce in bite sizes to about 1/2 full. Add 1 1/2 green peppers, then add green onions.
Follow with celery, then drained peas.
"Ice" with lots of mayonnaise. Add grated boiled egg across the top. Add grated Longhorn cheese and sprinkle bacon bits over the entire salad.
Serves 8 adults heartily.

title: noodle loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased loaf pan or angel food cake pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: best ever salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in hot water and add cream cheese and marshmallows.
Pour into a casserole; let stand until set.
Mix pineapple, nuts and whipped cream and pour over lemon jello. Dissolve cherry jello in hot water.
When cool, pour on top of pineapple mixture.

title: potluck
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until brown; drain.
Add salt, pepper, soup and water.
Fix macaroni and cheese as directed, but add 1/2 cup milk more than directed.
Combine.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Simmer vegetables in water and bouillon cubes for 10 minutes. Do not drain.
Make a white sauce with the flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Add to vegetables.
Then add cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in the desired meat.

title: queen of bread pudding
directions: Mix together brown sugar and water. Put in a baking dish. Add bits of butter. Add 4 to 6 slices of bread cut into cubes. Mix eggs, nutmeg, vanilla, milk and cinnamon. Pour over bread mixture. Do not stir. Place bits of butter on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: chuck's chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips and sugar mixture. Pour 1/2 of the batter into a 9 x 13 greased pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar mix. Sprinkle with half of the chocolate chips. Pour remaining batter on top and repeat with the cinnamon/sugar mix and with the chocolate chips. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hamburger rice hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery.
Add mushrooms, rice and seasonings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jackie's green chili
directions: Cook 12 hours in a crock-pot.
Serve over burritos.
Top with lettuce, tomato and grated cheese.

title: corn bread bundt cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar and other ingredients.
Mix good and pour into a sprayed pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and blend in shortening. Dissolve yeast in slightly warmed buttermilk.
Combine dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Mix quickly.
Turn out onto a floured board and knead 20 to 30 strokes.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut and dip in melted butter.
Place 2 biscuits atop each other. Cover and let rise in warm place for 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Add all ingredients, then add enough flour to make dough stiff. Roll and cut into desired size.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: people chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo together. Pour over cereal and mix carefully. Let cool. When cool, toss in brown paper bag with powdered sugar.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add
eggs
one at a time, beating well. Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavoring and baking powder.
Beat well.
Bake in a tube pan for 1
hour
and
35 minutes at 300°.
Do not preheat oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and salt in water until well done; drain. Add egg and butter.
Add water chestnuts.
Put in greased casserole in layers; make layer of squash mixture, layer of bread crumbs or stuffing and layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot throughout and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spell-breaker candy squares
directions: Melt chocolate pieces over hot water or in microwave.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares.
For a different taste, substitute 1/2 cup peanut butter chips for 1/2 cup of the chocolate chips.

title: first place fudge
directions: Melt
cheese
and butter in saucepan; mix well.
Stir in 10x sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer; stir in pecans.
Spread
in
buttered
1/2 x 12-inch pan. Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Yields: 3 1/4 pounds.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Season, boil and debone fryer. Heat the mushroom soup, chicken soup and tomatoes. Butter casserole dish. Layer crushed Doritos, chicken and soup until all used. Top with Velveeta cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add slightly beaten eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, milk and flavoring.
Bake in cold oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crisp onion-roasted potatoes
directions: In shallow baking dish, blend all ingredients, except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly.
Bake, stirring potatoes occasionally, about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped parsley.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute pepper and mushrooms.
Add flour, then broth; cook until thickened.
Add cream, sherry, salt and turkey.
Fold in cooked spaghetti.
Cook in shallow casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chocolate) in a large bowl.
Melt chocolate over low heat (may thin by adding 2 Tbsp. crisco shortening).
Pour over cereal and coat.
Pour out onto wax paper to cool.
After cooling, break apart and store in container.

title: steamed broccoli
directions: "Put in pot.
Put hot water (about 1 cup).
Cook on top of stove about 12 minutes.
Sometimes Mama puts cheese on it.
Then you eat it."

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar and mayonnaise.
Boil until thick.
Add Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and pimentos; mix well.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir into the creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Arrange on 3 or 4 heavy cooking sheets.
Add topping (any combination), ending with cheese.

title: healthy oat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine flour, oat bran, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In small bowl, combine milk, oil, orange peel and egg.
Blend well.
Add milk mixture all at once; stir just until moistened.
Stir in apple, dates and walnuts.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix first 3 ingredients, salt and pepper.
Pour into a Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Bisquick and enough milk to make a semi-thin (to be able to pour) mixture. Pour this over the vegetable mixture and bake for about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and dot with butter.

title: guinata-an with rice balls
directions: Pare the sweet potatoes, gabi and ube and cut them into 1/2-inch cubes. Peel the bananas and cut into slices, crosswise. Cut the nangka into strips. Boil the sweet potatoes, gabi and ube in 3 cups coconut milk. Form the malagkit rice into small balls and drop them in the boiling mixture. Then add the bananas, nangka, tapioca, anis and sugar. Simmer until cooked, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking and burning. About 5 minutes before serving, add the rest of the coconut milk. Heat through and serve.

title: ultra open-faced burgers
directions: Combine meat, 1/4 cup sour cream, 3 tablespoons cheese and seasonings; mix lightly.
Shape into 4 patties.
Broil on both sides to desired doneness.
Combine remaining sour cream, cheese and parsley in small saucepan; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Serve patties on muffin halves.
Top with sour cream mixture.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart deep baking dish. Heat milk in 1-quart saucepan over medium heat just until small bubbles start to form around edge.
(Do not boil!)
Add cereal and stir about 30 seconds until mixture starts to thicken.
Remove from heat; add cheese and stir until melted.
Add egg yolks; stir until blended.
Stir in spinach, ham and onions.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Fold egg whites into Cream of Wheat mixture with rubber spatula.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In a 3 quart saucepan, saute rice, onion, mushroom pieces, celery, celery leaves and spices in butter.
Add water.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: coconut slush cake
directions: Cook cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan.
While cake is hot, pour boiling mixture of coconut, milk, Eagle Brand milk and flavoring over cake.
Spread Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut after cake has been completely cooled.
Refrigerate until served.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well all ingredients except pecans.
Roll into a ball, then roll in pecans until covered.
Chill before serving.

title: valerie's ham-broccoli pie
directions: You will need one 9-inch deep dish pie crust.

title: crisp cole slaw
directions: Cook last 6 ingredients until dissolved. Pour while hot over cabbage. Cool. Will keep well in tightly closed container in refrigerator for several days.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix together the ingredients, except meat. Place meat in container and cover with marinade, piercing with fork. Marinate overnight in covered container in refrigerator. Remove meat strips. Drain slightly. Place on rack, making sure strips do not overlap. Place rack over cookie sheet in 150° to 175° oven. Bake for 3 1/2 hours. Remove from oven; cool and store in covered container in refrigerator. Must be refrigerated since it does not have preservatives!

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine crumbs and butter.
Pat firmly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add milk; beat until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
In a small bowl, toss together 1/2 cup chips with flour to coat.
Stir into cheese mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top.
Bake 1 hour or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool to room temperature; chill. Remove side of pan.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix the ground chuck, rice, onion, salt and pepper together. Scald cabbage and take off leaves.
Stuff each leave with chuck mixture.
Put in pot and cover with water, bring to a boil.
Add tomato paste, cook on low for 2 hours.
Prepare same way for pressure cooker, except pressure cook for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook hen until tender, remove bones and dice meat.
Mix meat with soup.
Set aside broth to cool.
Crumble bread and mix with salt, pepper, celery, sage and onion.
Moisten with cooled broth. Place half the crumb mixture over bottom of a 9 x 15-inch pan. Cover with chicken and soup mixture.
Mix beaten eggs into the remaining dressing and put evenly over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cape may blueberry cake
directions: Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a bowl, stir together flour, 1/3 cup sugar and baking powder.
Stir 1/2 cup butter, egg and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla until combined.
Sprinkle evenly in prepared pan; cover with blueberries.
In a bowl, stir together 2 cups sour cream, 2 egg yolks, remaining 1/3 cup sugar, remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1/4 teaspoon cardamom and lemon peel; pour evenly over blueberries.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly brown around the edges.
Cool completely.

title: celestial potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, celery, turnip, onion, vegetable flakes, salt and pepper; cover with water and simmer 30 minutes. In another saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour; add a small amount of liquid from potato mixture to form a paste.
Cool and stir in milk and sour cream.
When vegetables are cooked, mash or puree them and add flour and milk mixture.
Do not boil.
Serve; sprinkle with bacon.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable marinate
directions: Mix and add to vegetables. Let marinate 12 hours.

title: death by chocolate
directions: * Four boxes of Jell-O instant chocolate or chocolate fudge pudding can be substituted for mousse.

title: one dish meal
directions: Fry sausage, but not vegetables.
Mix vegetables with soup and fried sausage.
Cover and bake until done; if dry, just add water.

title: pork chop and potato dinner
directions: Put potatoes into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine soup, milk, onions, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.

title: lenola vidrine's rice cooker casserole
directions: Season to taste.
Place in rice cooker and cook as you would rice.

title: mandarin orange jello
directions: Bring water, Jell-O and tapioca to a boil.
Boil for one minute.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and mandarin oranges.
Let set in fridge.
Top with additional Cool Whip and chopped nuts or chocolate chips.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix the sugar and oil and beat. Add the eggs and vanilla. Sift together in a separate bowl the flour, salt and baking soda. Mix dry ingredients into wet mixture. Beat until smooth. Batter will be stiff. Add the apples, nuts, coconut and flavoring.
Mix together. Bake in greased and floured large tube pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Test for doneness.
Coll in pan 1/2 hour before removing. Frost with cream cheese icing, if desired.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler or microwave.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine oil, sugar and chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each egg. Add vanilla.
Blend thoroughly with sifted dry ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful into confectioners sugar.
Coat and shape balls.
Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack and store in airtight container.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine. Add buttermilk and soda, then flour and vanilla. Pour into greased cake pan and bake in 350° oven until toothpick comes out clean.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until lightly browned.
In slow cooker (crock-pot), combine onions, bouillon, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Top each bowl of soup with toasted French bread.
Top the toast with sliced cheese of your choice (Gruyere recommended).
Place bowls under broiler or microwave until cheese is melted.
Serves 4.

title: dot's chicken
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place uncooked chicken in pan.
Top each chicken cutlet with a piece of cheese.
Combine soup, Sauterne (or white wine of choice) and water.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle stuffing.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: taco soup(vegetarian)
directions: In large saucepan, brown the ground meat substitute with the chopped onion in cooking spray. Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Mix the jellos, water and 7-Up.
Let cool.
Add marshmallows, crushed pineapple and bananas.
Let set.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Mix all together, just until moist. Fry in skillet sprayed well with Pam, until browned on both sides.

title: hershey brownies
directions: Mix and bake in a large cookie sheet at 325° for 15 minutes. Then test.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Combine Karo syrup and bourbon. Mix into dry ingredients.
Roll into balls and sprinkle or roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello, quick jell as directed on box.
Add pineapple, cherries, nuts and Equal.
Let stand until firm.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 1 minute at lowest speed on mixer.
Pour in pie shell.
Chill 3 hours.

title: hummingbird nectar
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Bring to a boil; cool completely.
Put in hummingbird feeder.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Let buttermilk come to room temperature.
Then dissolve yeast in it.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Sift dry ingredients together and blend smoothly.
Mix liquid into flour mixture and knead lightly.
Roll out dough on lightly floured board.
Shape like Parker House roll or any shape desired.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Set in warm place to rise until light for 1 1/2 hours or more if needed.
Bake in hot 425° oven until well browned and done, approximately 20 minutes.
Yields about 36 rolls.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine broth, onion, potatoes and dillweed.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 50 minutes.
Place 1/2 of mixture in blender and blend until smooth.
Add to rest of mixture.
In another pot, melt margarine.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper or milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add to soup; cook until heated through.
Add milk, salt and pepper to taste, if needed.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and then bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled jalapeno peppers
directions: Pack peppers in clean sterilized jars. Mix next 3 ingredients in a sauce pan. Bring to a hard boil, pour over peppers. Seal with hot lids. These are good to eat with chip dip and corn chips or use as very hot pepper sauce.

title: german sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in a large glass/stainless steel bowl or pot.
Add everything but gingersnaps and sugar.
Let stand 36 hours in refrigerator (24 hours for milder flavor).
Turn 2 times a day. Remove meat, brown in shortening.
Add 2 1/2 cups strained vinegar mixture, gingersnaps and sugar.
Cover.
Cook slowly 2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Add water if necessary.

title: chili cranberry chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside. In large skillet, slowly brown chicken on both sides in oil. Pour reserved chili sauce mixture over chicken. Simmer, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes or until chicken is cooked and sauce is desired consistency. Turn and baste occasionally. Makes 4 to 6 servings (about 1 cup sauce).

title: steak diane
directions: Trim steaks and pound between pieces of wax paper to reduce them to 1/4 inch thick.
Crush drained green peppercorns with spoon and spread on both sides of steak or use ground black pepper.
Add a few drops of soy sauce and olive oil.

title: mamaw's cookies(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and unbeaten eggs; beat until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add nuts.
Gradually add to sugar mixture.
Drop cookie dough into an ungreased pan and bake the cookies until light brown at 400°.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips; stir in peanut butter.
Mix until well blended.
Pour over cereal and stir until well coated. Put in large container with 10x sugar and shake until well coated.

title: hurry up ketchup
directions: Mix together in small bowl.
Store in airtight container in the refrigerator.
Keeps 1 week.
Yield:
1 3/4 cups.

title: corn meal yeast bread
directions: Scald milk and add oleo, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm in large mixer bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
(I use part of sugar with yeast to dissolve it.)
Add yeast and eggs to milk and mix.
Beat in 2 cups flour and the corn meal for 2 minutes. Gradually add flour until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out on floured board and knead about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and grease top of dough.
Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down and let rest 10 minutes.
Divide into 2 or 3 balls (according to size of your pans) and roll each piece into rectangle.
From short side roll into tight roll.
Pinch seams, turn under ends and pinch.
Place in greased pans.
Brush with lightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
That is too hot for my oven, and after about 10 minutes, I turn it down to 350°.
May place a sheet of foil over the loaves the last few minutes if it is getting too brown.
Remove from pans, cool on rack.

title: sausage balls
directions: Crumble and cook sausage; drain well.
Grate cheese and blend with Bisquick; add egg to sausage and blend with Bisquick and cheese.
Knead until soft dough; roll into balls.
You may freeze or cook immediately.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix the sour cream and taco sauce together, spread on a sheet pan.
Fry hamburger well, drain grease and pat hamburger with paper towels to remove all excess grease.
Spread meat over cream cheese mixture.
Layer the tomatoes, lettuce and green peppers over mixture and top with cheese.
Serve with the chips.
It's wonderful at parties.

title: baked german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp; drain, reserving 1/4 cup bacon drippings.
Saute celery, onion and salt in reserved drippings in skillet.
Stir in flour.
Add sugar, vinegar, pepper and water.
Bring to boil.
Pour over bacon and potatoes in 3-quart baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Approximate per serving:
Cal 150; T fat 8 g; 44% calories from fat; prot 3 g; carbo 19 g; fiber 1 g; chol 33 mg; sodium 683 mg.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown
beef,
onion
and
pepper until tender.	Add all other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with foil (put a few
holes in the
foil).
Bake at 325° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine egg yolks and condensed milk, mixing well.
Add lime juice; blend well.
Turn into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and gradually add sugar.
Swirl onto pie spreading to edge of pie shell all around.
Bake in 300° oven until meringue is pale honey-colored.

title: sweet potato-apple bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 1-quart shallow baking dish. In small bowl, combine brown sugar, cinnamon and salt; set aside. Cut sweet potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange half in baking dish.
Cover with apples.
Sprinkle half the brown sugar mixture over apples.
Top with remaining sweet potato slices.
Sprinkle with remaining brown sugar.
Spoon on 2 tablespoons of melted butter or margarine.
Cover and bake 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: josie's chess pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar, stir in melted butter.
Add other ingredients.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into raw pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas peppered steak
directions: Tenderize steak or have it tenderized.
Cut into serving pieces.
Rub on salt and pepper.
Sear steak just until pink is gone in a small amount of oil in hot skillet.
Transfer to baking dish.
Spread soup over steak.
Slice jalapenos thin and sprinkle over cheese soup.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix cottage cheese and eggs together; set aside.
Put oil in skillet.
Add garlic and onion.
Cook until clear.
Add beef; cook until brown and drain.
Add salt, pepper, parsley and rosemary. Add tomato paste and water and simmer until done.
At same time boil noodles until done.

title: danish puffs
directions: Mix like pie crust to form a ball the first 3 ingredients.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix whipped cream and drained pineapple by hand.
Gradually add Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Pour in crust and chill for 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: mock cabbage roll casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter in skillet.
Add ground beef and seasonings.
Cook until beef is heated through, stirring frequently.
Do not brown.
Layer half the cabbage and all the ground beef mixture in 2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cabbage and soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with graham crackers.
Try to fill bottom layer as close as possible.
Mix pudding and milk. Add Cool Whip to this mixture.
Begin layers of pudding and crackers.
First layer crackers, second layer 1/2 pudding, third layer crackers, fourth layer 1/2 pudding, fifth layer crackers, sixth layer chocolate frosting.

title: 1-2-3-4 casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: moon cake
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil; add flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Cool 10 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Spread in a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Cool.

title: authentic hungarian christmas muffins
directions: Mix 1/2 flour, sugar, salt and yeast in bowl.
Heat milk in heavy saucepan until warm.
Mix with remaining flour, adding more, if needed, to form smooth ball.
Turn onto floured board and knead 5 minutes.
Allow to rest in an oiled bowl, covered, approximately 1 to 2 hours.
When dough doubles, turn onto clean buttered counter.
Add raisins, nuts, coconut, vanilla and almond extract. Using a chopper or a chef's knife, chop into bits and coarse chunks.
Put a handful in greased muffin pan (until cup is 1/2 full).
Allow to rest and rise 1 hour.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° until golden.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while warm.
